          "label": "GPT 5.5",
          "content": "# BU3A Keyword Opportunity and Optimization Analysis\n\nQuestion: I need to do a deep analysis on the account specifically the portfolio BU3A. The client is looking for a keyword analysis to identify opportunities, challenges, and changes we can make to improve BU3A performance\n\nBusiness data used: campaign-level advertising performance, keyword, search-term, and targeting performance, campaign configuration, budget, and status snapshots. Time basis: 2025-04-07/2025-05-07; 2025-04-07/2025-05-06; 2025-04-07/2025-05-05. Monetary values follow the numeric currency basis present in the business data; no additional FX conversion was applied.\n\n## Executive read\n\nBU3A has a large volume of keyword traffic, but efficiency is uneven. Across the keyword summary, the business dataset shows 69,838,227 impressions, 608,861 clicks, $723,413.66 spend, $3,228,342.63 sales, 105,687 orders, and an aggregate ACOS of 22.4%. The strongest path to improve BU3A is not to cut traffic broadly; it is to move budget and bids toward the high-order, low-ACOS terms while cleaning up no-order and high-ACOS spend.\n\n## Keywords to scale\n\n| keyword | match type | clicks | orders | spend | sales | ACOS | CVR |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| blanket | EXACT | 19,126 | 3,800 | $20,774.47 | $107,540.18 | 19.3% | 19.9% |\n| duvet insert | EXACT | 11,019 | 2,167 | $19,682.61 | $84,435.88 | 23.3% | 19.7% |\n| throw blanket | EXACT | 9,786 | 1,501 | $8,105.79 | $36,281.23 | 22.3% | 15.3% |\n| bedsure | EXACT | 3,401 | 872 | $3,961.20 | $36,073.40 | 11.0% | 25.6% |\n| bedsure comforter | EXACT | 3,959 | 710 | $4,295.20 | $32,564.35 | 13.2% | 17.9% |\n| blanket | BROAD | 6,434 | 880 | $4,045.47 | $24,527.25 | 16.5% | 13.7% |\n| bedsure sheets | BROAD | 3,414 | 750 | $2,162.01 | $23,562.80 | 9.2% | 22.0% |\n| bedsure blanket | BROAD | 3,279 | 792 | $1,965.95 | $22,346.51 | 8.8% | 24.2% |\n\nRecommended action: keep these terms active, protect exact-match coverage, and increase bids/budgets in small steps where impression share is constrained. `blanket`, `duvet insert`, `throw blanket`, `bedsure`, `bedsure comforter`, and `bedsure sheets` are the clearest scale candidates in this business data because they combine meaningful order volume with manageable ACOS.\n\n## Keywords/search targets to fix\n\nHigh-spend terms with zero orders:\n\n| keyword | match type | clicks | spend | sales | action |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| king bedsure duvet | EXACT | 40 | $82.30 | $0.00 | negate or pause if not strategically required |\n| mother's day gifts | EXACT | 34 | $75.38 | $0.00 | negate or pause if not strategically required |\n| king size summer blanket | EXACT | 36 | $62.42 | $0.00 | negate or pause if not strategically required |\n| hotel comforter queen | EXACT | 26 | $53.53 | $0.00 | negate or pause if not strategically required |\n| +bed+comforter | BROAD | 40 | $50.34 | $0.00 | negate or pause if not strategically required |\n\nHigh-ACOS terms with orders:\n\n| keyword | match type | clicks | orders | spend | sales | ACOS | action |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| birthday gifts for women | EXACT | 1,211 | 216 | $2,248.62 | $3,638.11 | 61.8% | lower bid 15-30% and isolate query intent |\n| cotton+sheets | BROAD | 753 | 38 | $1,511.66 | $2,373.42 | 63.7% | lower bid 15-30% and isolate query intent |\n| 100 cotton sheets | EXACT | 388 | 21 | $1,057.84 | $1,206.97 | 87.6% | lower bid 15-30% and isolate query intent |\n| cotton sheets | EXACT | 339 | 18 | $775.73 | $1,051.62 | 73.8% | lower bid 15-30% and isolate query intent |\n| twin xl mattress topper | EXACT | 409 | 25 | $703.74 | $884.44 | 79.6% | lower bid 15-30% and isolate query intent |\n| twin xl mattress topper | BROAD | 647 | 28 | $609.59 | $893.76 | 68.2% | lower bid 15-30% and isolate query intent |\n\n## Changes to make\n\n1. Expand exact-match campaigns for the proven generic bed/sleep terms that are already converting under ACOS control.\n2. Separate high-volume broad/phrase terms from exact terms so budget does not get consumed by exploratory traffic before exact winners serve.\n3. Add negatives for no-order terms after checking whether they are brand-defense or competitor-defense terms.\n4. Reduce bids on terms above 60% ACOS before pausing; pause only when spend is material and conversion quality remains weak.\n5. Use search-term mining to split mixed terms into product-type clusters: cooling blanket, sheet set, pillow, duvet/comforter.\n6. Keep BU3A budget flexible: reallocate spend from the zero-order bucket into the scale list above, then watch ACOS and order volume together.\n"
