          "content": "# Campaigns with ACOS > 30% and Optimization Dimensions\n\n## Data window & scope\n- Campaign-level performance report covering **April 2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (trailing 30 days)**, 2,659 date-bucketed rows aggregated to the campaign.\n- Account: Bedsure (US + CA). Currency mix: ~91% USD, ~9% CAD — numbers below are in the reported currency as-is, and CAD rows are marked where they appear in top-line tables.\n- (Note on window: the earlier-month April-2025 snapshot is also available for this account; I standardized on the most recent 30-day window so conclusions reflect current state.)\n\n## Headline counts\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Total campaigns | 2,659 |\n| With any sales | 2,306 |\n| **Campaigns with ACOS > 30%** | **759** |\n| Spend in the ACOS > 30% cohort | ~$779,311 |\n| Sales in the ACOS > 30% cohort | ~$1,941,353 |\n| **Blended ACOS of the > 30% cohort** | **40.1%** |\n\n### ACOS distribution inside the > 30% cohort\n\n| ACOS band | Campaigns |\n|---|---|\n| 30% – 50% (marginal) | 521 |\n| 50% – 100% | 194 |\n| 100% – 200% | 34 |\n| > 200% | 10 |\n\n## Highest-leverage cohort (top spenders with ACOS > 30%)\n\nThese 12 campaigns concentrate the dollars and should be treated first.\n\n| Campaign (trunc.) | ACOS | Spend | Sales | CVR | CPC |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| Xnurta AI CHY【床单-压花/竹纤维/深笠高】SB精准-sheets+QU | 41.2% | $25,986 | $63,091 | 26.7% | $2.95 |\n| 小熊【天然床单组】SB精准-bamboo sheets-旗舰店 | 58.0% | $20,515 | $35,387 | 16.8% | $6.94 |\n| Xnurta AI sy【毯子组】SB精准-throw 大词 | 40.9% | $15,736 | $38,462 | 21.7% | $2.17 |\n| Xnurta AI 荣芳【枕套组-色丁-QU-鹿皮米】SP精准-silk pillow-企业购 | 42.0% | $14,789 | $35,205 | 39.5% | $1.78 |\n| Xnurta AI 荣芳【枕套组-色丁-QU-白色】SP精准-satin pillowcase-企业购 | 38.7% | $12,013 | $31,048 | 47.0% | $1.93 |\n| ZH-CXM【睡眠枕-化纤枕-QU-白色-2pk】SB精准-pillows queen | 33.0% | $10,686 | $32,405 | 32.2% | $3.42 |\n| Xnurta AI 小熊【天然床单组】SB广泛-cooling+规格 | 33.3% | $10,381 | $31,220 | 20.3% | $4.80 |\n| Xnurta AI SY【毛毯-工艺绒类毯-TH-白色】SP精准-blanket-AMC | 35.4% | $9,517 | $26,880 | 17.9% | $1.45 |\n| 荣芳【枕套组】SB精准-satin 核心词 | 37.7% | $9,369 | $24,879 | 49.1% | $2.04 |\n| BU3A-sy【毯子组】SB精准-cooling blankets for hot sleepers | 54.4% | $9,084 | $16,703 | 12.8% | $3.08 |\n| BU3A-GH【被子-全涤-QU+KI-白色】SP类目-多件套-防御 | 32.0% | $8,855 | $27,709 | 6.3% | $1.00 |\n| Xnurta AI 小熊【天然床单组】SB广泛-sheets+cooling | 34.2% | $8,733 | $25,504 | 17.5% | $3.73 |\n\nThese 12 campaigns together account for ~$155K of spend. Pulling their blended ACOS from ~40% down to 28% is worth roughly $15K/month with minimal sales sacrifice.\n\n## Worst-ACOS outliers (dollar-small, but diagnostically clear)\n\n| Campaign (trunc.) | ACOS | Spend | Sales | CVR | CPC | Pathology |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| CHY【床单-持续凉感抗菌-QU-芯片灰】SP精准-cooling+QU | 838% | $109 | $13 | 2.8% | $3.03 | CPC $3 on ASIN that can't carry it |\n| GH【被子-撞色 260gsm-QU-灰色】SP广泛-QU+duvet | 606% | $60 | $10 | 3.1% | $1.89 | Broad match pulling low-intent traffic |\n| 小熊【天然床笠】SB广泛-fitted sheets+规格 | 385% | $193 | $50 | 1.4% | $2.64 | SB creative/search-term mismatch |\n| GH【被子-锦氨双面凉感-QU-港湾灰】SBV精准-marshmallow comforter | 278% | $222 | $80 | 1.1% | $2.41 | SBV CPC too rich, poor landing fit |\n| Enos【床垫罩-磨毛布压花-TX-白色】SP精准-Dorm/college | 257% | $75 | $29 | 1.6% | $1.18 | Scenario keyword doesn't match ASIN |\n| 靠垫套-全棉壳-撞色荷叶边-2pack SP精准-属性词 | 241% | $65 | $27 | 1.1% | $0.75 | Ad group mixing too many intents |\n| BU3A-lyh【毛毯-兔毛-TH-榛果褐】SP广泛-Faux Fur | 213% | $149 | $70 | 0.8% | $1.23 | 0.8% CVR — keyword↔product irrelevance |\n| SY【毛毯-工艺绒类毯-TH-白色】SP词组-decor 拓流 | 211% | $441 | $209 | 2.9% | $1.15 | Exploration broad terms don't convert |\n| LYH【睡眠枕-化纤枕/O型枕】SB精准-cervical pillows | 207% | $293 | $142 | 3.3% | $3.19 | SB head term — CPC too expensive |\n| ZH【床垫罩-磨毛布压花-TX-白色】SBV广泛-dorm | 206% | $793 | $385 | 2.6% | $1.58 | Broad SBV on scenario terms, clear waste |\n\n## Optimization dimensions (what to do, per dimension)\n\nThe 759 high-ACOS campaigns, bucketed by the most plausible dominant failure mode:\n\n| Dimension | Campaigns flagged | What's wrong | Action |\n|---|---:|---|---|\n| **Bid level / CPC overbidding** (CPC > $2) | 263 | Bid too high for the ASIN's price point; common in SB/SBV and PT campaigns | Cut bids 20–40%. Switch fixed-bid → dynamic down-only. Recompute target bid = `AOV × target ACOS × CVR`. |\n| **Targeting / keyword relevance** (CVR < 5% with clicks) | 130 | Clicks arrive but don't convert — search terms or competitor ASINs don't match the product | Pull search-term reports; negate any term with > $5 spend and 0 orders; move profitable terms to exact in their own group; prune competitor PT to same-price-tier ASINs. |\n| **Creative / ad copy** (CTR < 0.3% on impressions > 500) | 99 | Impression supply is fine but the ad doesn't pull clicks | Refresh main image; test new SB headline; re-audit keyword→ASIN alignment (bad CTR often = wrong landing ASIN). |\n| **Waste spend** (spend > $50, orders < 3) | 39 | Campaigns burning cash with near-zero output | Pause or restructure to exact-match only. Reallocate the ~$5K monthly waste. |\n| **Marginal ACOS 30–50%** | 522 | Just over target — mostly a bid-calibration problem | Apply −10% bid across the band. Xnurta AI-managed campaigns in this band should have target ACOS pulled from their current ~35% setting down to ~28%. |\n\n## Key takeaways\n\n1. The problem is not concentrated in a few blow-ups. **69%** (522 of 759) of high-ACOS campaigns sit in the 30–50% band — a single account-wide **−10% bid sweep** is the highest-ROI first move.\n2. The **top-12 high-spend / ACOS > 30% campaigns** own ~20% of the over-threshold spend. These need campaign-by-campaign attention, not a sweep.\n3. **Xnurta AI-managed campaigns** repeatedly surface in the 33–42% ACOS band. Tighten their target ACOS by 5–7 percentage points.\n4. **SB/SBV head-term campaigns** (小熊 bamboo sheets SB, BU3A-LYH cervical pillows SB, Xnurta AI sy throw SB) are the most expensive-CPC offenders. Consider replacing head terms with mid-long-tail, or running SP on the head terms instead of SB.\n5. The **39 waste-spend campaigns** are ~$5K/month of near-zero-return spend — pausing is essentially free money back.\n\n## What additional data would sharpen this further\n\n- Keyword- and search-term-level report for the 759 high-ACOS campaigns (confirms which exact terms inflate CPC / drive low CVR).\n- Placement report (top-of-search vs product-pages vs rest-of-search) — decides whether top-of-search modifiers should be pulled.\n- Current keyword bids and budget caps — converts % bid-down recommendations into exact new-bid values.\n- ASIN price and margin — computes true target ACOS and break-even bid per campaign.\n- Previous 30-day ACOS for each campaign — separates \"structurally high ACOS\" from \"recently degraded\".\n"
