          "content": "# Period-over-Period Keyword CVR Comparison and Next Steps\n\n## Data window & scope\n- **Current period**: 2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days). 2,635 keyword × campaign combos.\n- **Prior period**: 2026-03-09 → 2026-04-07 (30 days). 2,958 keyword × campaign combos.\n- **Overlap**: 2,297 keyword × campaign combos active in both periods.\n\n## Account-level period-over-period\n\n| | Prior (Mar-09 → Apr-07) | Current (Apr-08 → May-07) | Δ |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| Spend | $30,073 | $54,741 | **+82%** |\n| Sales | $192,489 | $281,772 | **+46%** |\n| ACOS | 15.6% | **19.4%** | +3.8 pp |\n| CVR | 20.3% | **14.4%** | **−5.9 pp** |\n\nTwo structural shifts at the account level:\n- **Spend almost doubled** while sales grew 46% → CPC / auction cost inflated or new less-efficient keywords were added.\n- **CVR fell 5.9 pp**. The question (\"what's next for high-CVR keywords?\") is especially important given that compression — the winners need protection.\n\n## High-CVR keywords that improved further (64 total, top 15 by Δ)\n\nFilter: ≥ 20 clicks current, ≥ 10 clicks prior, current CVR ≥ 20%, CVR rose period-over-period.\n\n| Keyword | Match | Prior CVR | Current CVR | ΔCVR | Clicks | ACOS | Spend |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| hornady one shot | PHRASE | 37% | 76% | +39.5 | 34 | 2% | $17 |\n| amerelle | PHRASE | 20% | 52% | +31.7 | 25 | 6% | $21 |\n| petkins | PHRASE | 36% | 58% | +22.0 | 26 | 13% | $40 |\n| cooling pad for dogs | EXACT | 7% | 25% | +17.9 | 24 | 13% | $46 |\n| cooling mat for cats | EXACT | 5% | 22% | +17.2 | 40 | 13% | $54 |\n| wine drops | EXACT | 30% | 45% | +15.8 | 33 | 16% | $96 |\n| chillz | PHRASE | 10% | 23% | +13.9 | 47 | 8% | $48 |\n| dog tooth wipes | EXACT | 23% | 36% | +12.8 | 114 | 69% | $412 |\n| big and thick pet wipes | PHRASE | 35% | 48% | +12.7 | 23 | 20% | $43 |\n| musician practice glove | PHRASE | 22% | 32% | +10.4 | 90 | 13% | $54 |\n| asin=\"B07P6SNV19\" | PT | 38% | 47% | +8.6 | 66 | 4% | $25 |\n| dog cooling mat | EXACT | 13% | 22% | +8.6 | 326 | **14%** | **$636** |\n| petkin pet wipes | PHRASE | 32% | 40% | +8.6 | 42 | 15% | $46 |\n\n## Stable high-CVR keywords (17 total)\n\nFilter: current CVR ≥ 25%, Δ within ±5pp.\n\n| Keyword | Match | CVR (prior→cur) | Spend | Sales | ACOS |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| green pet | PHRASE | 32% → 29% | $2,199 | $31,035 | 7% |\n| drop it | PHRASE | 22% → 25% | $571 | $2,029 | 28% |\n| wine drops | EXACT | 42% → 39% | $465 | $1,412 | 33% |\n| wine drops remove sulfites and histamine | EXACT | 37% → 40% | $268 | $975 | 28% |\n| the green pet shop | PHRASE | 29% → 29% | $248 | $3,965 | 6% |\n| petkin | PHRASE | 41% → 40% | $231 | $1,472 | 16% |\n| belly bones | PHRASE | 49% → 48% | $172 | $1,508 | 11% |\n\n## High-CVR that's DECLINING (20 total, most actionable)\n\nFilter: current CVR ≥ 20%, CVR dropped ≥ 5pp.\n\n| Keyword | Match | CVR prior → current | ΔCVR | Clicks | ACOS | Spend |\n|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| petkin | PHRASE | 61% → 25% | −36.1 | 32 | 22% | $29 |\n| pearl x lacrosse ball | EXACT | 46% → 26% | −20.0 | 34 | 2% | $21 |\n| yogurt bones for dogs | PHRASE | 45% → 27% | −18.7 | 83 | 15% | $124 |\n| petkin (different ad group) | PHRASE | 42% → 24% | −18.0 | 34 | 40% | $52 |\n| belly bones for small dogs | EXACT | 49% → 32% | −16.9 | 28 | 11% | $30 |\n| dog tooth wipes | EXACT | 45% → 29% | −16.4 | 31 | 56% | $74 |\n| asin=\"B08LMMSQ83\" | PT | 51% → 35% | −16.2 | 46 | 7% | $27 |\n| greaseless lacrosse balls | EXACT | 40% → 24% | −15.5 | 25 | 11% | $22 |\n| drop it | EXACT | 67% → 52% | −14.8 | 27 | 3% | $12 |\n| drop it wine drops | EXACT | 42% → 30% | −11.2 | 23 | 9% | $19 |\n| tooth wipes for dogs | EXACT | 36% → 25% | −10.8 | 20 | **101%** | $79 |\n| big thick pet wipes | PHRASE | 44% → 34% | −10.0 | 122 | 28% | $233 |\n\n## Next-step adjustments for high-CVR keywords\n\n### A. The winners that improved (64 keywords) — scale, don't just hold\n- **Raise bids 15–25%** on keywords where CVR is rising AND ACOS is well below 25% (e.g., `dog cooling mat` EXACT: CVR 22%, ACOS 14%, 326 clicks — room to bid up).\n- Particularly aggressive on **brand terms rising in CVR**: `hornady one shot`, `amerelle`, `chillz`. These are defensive and cheap.\n- For the `cooling mat for cats` EXACT (5% → 22% CVR, only 40 clicks): this is a signal that cat-audience is responding. Add a dedicated cat-cooling-pad campaign (aligns with EV054 recommendation).\n\n### B. Stable high-CVR (17 keywords) — protect, slightly extend\n- These are foundational. Don't raise bids; extend *coverage* via longer-tail variants. E.g., `green pet` (29% CVR, $2.2K spend, 7% ACOS) supports adding `green pet shop mat`, `green pet cooling`, `green pet chillz`.\n- Top-of-search modifiers on these are safe to keep or increase modestly (+10%).\n\n### C. High-CVR declining (20 keywords) — **highest priority**\nThese were previously good and are now slipping. Three patterns:\n1. **CVR halved from the high 40s–60s to mid 20s on strong brand/name terms** (`petkin` PHRASE 61→25, `drop it` EXACT 67→52, `pearl x lacrosse ball` 46→26). This is almost always either (a) creative refresh without updating landing ASIN, (b) inventory stockout on the landing ASIN, or (c) competitor running brand-defense PT against these same search terms. **Investigate listing status and inventory immediately.**\n2. **`dog tooth wipes`** appears on both sides: current CVR 36% (up from 23%) on one campaign, but 29% (down from 45%) on another. The same keyword across two ad groups tells a split-test story — consolidate into the winning ad group.\n3. **`tooth wipes for dogs` ACOS 101%** with CVR declining — pause unless listing fix expected to close both gaps.\n\n### D. Cross-cutting: don't raise all bids just because account ACOS ticked up\nThe 5.9pp CVR drop at account level is the backdrop. Blanket bid-ups on \"high-CVR winners\" without first fixing the 20 declining ones will burn money as the conversion rate regresses.\n\n## Priority order of actions\n1. **Diagnose the 20 declining high-CVR keywords** (listing status, inventory, creative). Fix before spending more.\n2. **Raise bids 15–25% on the 15 scaleable improving winners** listed above — budget impact ~+$1.5K/mo, sales impact ~+$8–10K.\n3. **Add cat-audience campaign** around `cooling mat for cats`, `cooling pad for cats`.\n4. **Consolidate split-test ad groups** for keywords like `dog tooth wipes` that appear in both improvers and decliners.\n5. **Protect stable high-CVR brand terms** with longer-tail variants.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- Current keyword bids — to size the +15–25% moves.\n- Inventory / listing status per ASIN — to triage the declining-CVR cohort.\n- Search-term reports for the relevant auto/broad keywords — to explain CVR drops by query shift.\n- ASIN-level CVR over the same two periods — to separate \"keyword change\" from \"landing-page change\".\n- Impression share — to know whether the declining-CVR keywords are getting different (lower-quality) placement than before.\n"
