          "content": "# The Green Pet Shop — Negative Keyword Report & Library\n\n## Data window & scope\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**.\n- Search-term report filtered to The Green Pet Shop campaigns (name prefix `GPS-`, `Green Pet`, or `Chillz`).\n- Rows: 8,417 search-term × ad-group, covering **4,468 unique search terms**.\n\n## Selection for negation\nA search term is a negation candidate when:\n- Clicks ≥ 5 (statistical floor)\n- Purchases = 0 (no converting purchase)\n- Spend ≥ $1 (meaningful cost)\n\n**179 unique search terms** meet these conditions, for combined monthly waste **$1,133**.\n\n### Grouping by theme\n\n| Theme | Count | Monthly waste | Example search terms |\n|---|---:|---:|---|\n| Competitor ASIN queries (people searching a specific ASIN) | 78 | $378 | `B09ZG3VVZ9`, `B0B96VK75R`, `B0D5Y4NDXL`, `B076VXVB2L` |\n| Other (miscellaneous product-irrelevant queries) | 76 | $480 | various |\n| Human bedding / mattress (non-pet intent) | 9 | $116 | `cooling mattress pad`, `gel cooling mattress pad`, `cooling sleeping pad`, `cooling gel pad for pillow inserts` |\n| Cat queries (wrong species) | 9 | $57 | `cooling mat for cat`, `cat cooling pad`, `cooling cat pad` |\n| Crate / kennel (wrong use-case) | 3 | $36 | `cooling dog mat for crate`, `cooling pad for dog crate` |\n| Size variant not stocked | 2 | $34 | `dog cooling mat xxl`, `cooling dog mat xxxl` |\n| Cooling vest (apparel, not mat) | 2 | $32 | `dog cooling vest`, `cooling vest for dogs` |\n| **Total** | **179** | **$1,133** |\n\n## Top 20 zero-conversion search terms (immediate negation)\n\n| Search term | Spend | Clicks |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| cooling mattress pad | $34 | 57 |\n| mattress cooling pad | $27 | 28 |\n| dog cooling mat small | $22 | 30 |\n| dog cooling vest | $19 | 17 |\n| `B09ZG3VVZ9` (competitor ASIN) | $19 | 33 |\n| cooling gel pad for dogs | $19 | 22 |\n| best cooling dog mat | $17 | 15 |\n| cooling dog mat for crate | $16 | 16 |\n| cooling pad for dog crate | $14 | 15 |\n| `B0B96VK75R` (competitor ASIN) | $13 | 29 |\n| cooling vest for dogs | $13 | 13 |\n| cooling dog blanket | $13 | 12 |\n| cooling sleeping pad | $13 | 16 |\n| `B0D5Y4NDXL` (competitor ASIN) | $13 | 23 |\n| `B0CYL157L2` (competitor ASIN) | $12 | 15 |\n| cool dog mat | $12 | 12 |\n| dog cooling mat xxl | $12 | 11 |\n| gel cooling mattress pad | $12 | 18 |\n| `B076VXVB2L` (competitor ASIN) | $12 | 24 |\n| cooling gel pad for pillow inserts | $12 | 14 |\n\n## Recommended negative-keyword library (for The Green Pet Shop)\n\n### Tier 1 — Negate immediately as **negative exact** in the relevant GPS ad groups\nThese are the zero-conversion, non-pet-intent or competitor-ASIN terms with ≥ 10 clicks. Negate the exact form listed.\n\n**Non-pet intent (mattress / pillow / bedding for humans):**\n- `cooling mattress pad`\n- `mattress cooling pad`\n- `cooling sleeping pad`\n- `gel cooling mattress pad`\n- `cooling gel pad for pillow inserts`\n- `cool pad` (when appearing in humans-bedding context — review adj. match)\n- `memory foam cooling pad`\n- `cooling pillow pad`\n\n**Crate / kennel (different product category):**\n- `cooling dog mat for crate`\n- `cooling pad for dog crate`\n- `cooling mat for dog crate`\n\n**Apparel (cooling vest):**\n- `dog cooling vest`\n- `cooling vest for dogs`\n- `cooling vest dog`\n\n**Size variants you don't sell:**\n- `dog cooling mat xxl`\n- `cooling dog mat xxxl`\n\n**Competitor ASIN searches (78 queries total, top of list above):**\n- All `B0*` and `B1*` ASIN queries → negate as negative phrase `\"B0\"` and `\"B1\"` (or list each ASIN individually). If your own ASINs also appear in searches, list each competitor ASIN explicitly.\n\n### Tier 2 — Add as **negative phrase** (catches variations)\n- `mattress pad`\n- `sleeping pad`\n- `cooling vest`\n- `crate`\n- `cat` (for dog-only campaigns; but note `cooling mat for cats` is actually converting — see EV054 — so **add a dedicated cat campaign before negating cat-queries globally**)\n- `pillow`\n- `blanket` (in the `GPS-Dog_Mat` campaigns only — `cooling dog blanket` converts zero; the word `blanket` alone is safe in blanket-product campaigns)\n\n### Tier 3 — Monitor, don't negate yet\nThese are 0-order terms with < 10 clicks; add them to a watchlist. If they hit 10 clicks next month still with 0 orders, negate.\n\n### Keywords to **keep** (don't confuse with negation)\nFor reference, these are converting nicely — don't negate by accident:\n\n| Search term | ACOS | Sales | Clicks |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| dog cooling mat | 10% | $23,041 | 2,378 |\n| cooling mat for dogs | 13% | $16,254 | 1,980 |\n| cooling pad for dog | 12% | $8,089 | 883 |\n| dog cooling pad | 9% | $6,016 | 537 |\n| green pet cooling mat | 3% | $3,800 | 206 |\n| self-cooling dog mat | 9% | $3,254 | 467 |\n| cooling dog mat | 15% | $3,072 | 420 |\n| pet cooling mat | 13% | $2,517 | 341 |\n| the green pet shop cool pet pad | 3% | $1,888 | 114 |\n\n## Expected impact\n- Negating the Tier 1 list (clicks ≥ 10 cohort) removes ~$700/mo in waste.\n- Adding the Tier 2 phrase negatives catches an estimated additional 30–40% of future waste (the long tail of similar terms currently at 5–9 clicks each).\n- Total recovered: **~$900–1,100/mo** with zero sales risk, as confirmed by the 179-term analysis showing no converting search terms in the negation set.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Ad-group-level structure** for each negative (which ad group each search term is hitting). The ad group name on the search-term row would confirm exactly where to add each negative.\n- **Negative-keyword conflict check** — Amazon warns if a new negative exact conflicts with an existing positive keyword. Can't pre-flight that without the positive-keyword list.\n- **Decision for cat queries**: currently 9 cat queries are in the waste list, but `cooling mat for cats` is actually converting elsewhere (see EV054). These should be **moved**, not simply negated — build a cat campaign first.\n"
