          "label": "Gemini 3.1 Pro",
          "content": "# The Green Pet Shop: Negative Keyword Analysis & Library Strategy\n\n\nBased on the provided search term and campaign data for **The Green Pet Shop (GPS)**, I have analyzed the search queries triggering your ads to identify areas of wasted ad spend. \n\nTo optimize your campaigns, we need to implement a robust **Negative Keyword Strategy**. This report outlines specific search terms that should be negated immediately and provides a framework for building a scalable Negative Keyword Library.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Identified Negative Keyword Candidates\nBy analyzing search terms with clicks and spend but **zero sales**, I have categorized the immediate negative keyword candidates into four distinct groups. \n\n### A. Irrelevant Product Types (Format Mismatch)\nYour products are primarily cooling *mats* and *pads*. Search terms indicating a completely different product format are wasting your budget.\n\n| Search Term | Campaign | Clicks | Spend | Reason for Negation | Recommended Match Type |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `dog cooling vest ice` | GPS_Dog_Cooling_Mat_Training_Pads | 1 | $1.04 | User is looking for wearable apparel (vest), not a mat. | **Phrase:** \"vest\", \"vests\" |\n| `pet bean bag mat` | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad | 1 | $0.32 | User is looking for a plush/bean bag bed, not a gel cooling pad. | **Phrase:** \"bean bag\" |\n\n### B. Promo Code & Deal Seekers\nUsers searching for specific promo codes usually have low purchase intent unless they already have the code. They are looking for a discount, not shopping organically.\n\n| Search Term | Campaign | Clicks | Spend | Reason for Negation | Recommended Match Type |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `pet cooling mat 21.6 30 inches promo code swj2gjxy` | GPS_Dog_Cooling_Mat_Training_Pads | 1 | $0.71 | Low-intent query looking for a specific external discount. | **Phrase:** \"promo code\", \"coupon\" |\n\n### C. Underperforming Competitor ASINs\nAuto and Broad campaigns often bleed spend on competitor ASINs that do not convert. \n\n| Search Term (ASIN) | Campaign | Clicks | Spend | Reason for Negation | Recommended Match Type |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `B098L6X51Q` | CHILLZ_Cat_Dog_Cooling_Mat | 4 | $2.18 | Multiple clicks, zero sales. | **Exact:** B098L6X51Q |\n| `B09QC39Y89` | GPS_Cool_Pet_Pad | 1 | $0.49 | Zero sales. | **Exact:** B09QC39Y89 |\n\n### D. Highly Specific Mismatched Attributes\nIf a user searches for a highly specific color or feature that your product does not possess, they will click out of curiosity but bounce when they see the product details.\n\n| Search Term | Campaign | Clicks | Spend | Reason for Negation | Recommended Match Type |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `seafoam green cooling dog mat` | GPS_Pet_Pad_Cover | 1 | $1.00 | Unless GPS sells a specific \"seafoam green\" variant, this will not convert. | **Phrase:** \"seafoam green\" |\n\n*(Note: Conversely, do NOT negate terms like `gel cooling dog mat` or `chillow cooling pillow`, as the data shows these are driving high ROAS—59.98 and 9.84 respectively).*\n\n---\n\n## 2. Building Your Negative Keyword Library\nTo prevent future wasted spend, I recommend structuring a **Negative Keyword Library** in your Amazon Ads console. This allows you to apply lists across multiple campaigns instantly.\n\n### List 1: Universal Brand Negatives (Apply to ALL Campaigns)\nThese are terms that will *never* be relevant to The Green Pet Shop's current product line.\n*   **Phrase Match:** \n    *   `\"vest\"`\n    *   `\"vests\"`\n    *   `\"apparel\"`\n    *   `\"bean bag\"`\n    *   `\"promo code\"`\n    *   `\"coupon\"`\n    *   `\"cheap\"`\n    *   `\"free\"`\n\n### List 2: ASIN Exclusion List (Apply to Auto & Category Campaigns)\nCreate a running list of competitor ASINs that historically yield clicks but no sales. Based on current data, start with:\n*   **Exact Match:**\n    *   `B098L6X51Q`\n    *   `B09QC39Y89`\n*(Action: Update this list bi-weekly by filtering your Search Term Report for ASINs with >3 clicks and 0 orders).*\n\n### List 3: Species/Size Specific Negatives (Apply to specific Ad Groups)\nIf you have campaigns strictly dedicated to large dogs, you should negate cat terms, and vice versa.\n*   *Example:* The search term `cat crate bed mat` triggered in the `GPS_Pet_Pad_Cover` campaign. If this specific cover is sized/marketed exclusively for medium/large dogs, add `\"cat\"` and `\"kitten\"` as Phrase negatives to that specific campaign.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Next Steps & Recommendations\n\n1.  **Apply the Hit List:** Immediately add the Phrase and Exact match recommendations from Section 1 into your active campaigns (`GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad`, `GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover`, etc.).\n2.  **Create the Portfolios/Lists:** Go to the Amazon Ads console -> Targeting -> Negative Keyword Lists, and create the three lists outlined in Section 2.\n3.  **Harvesting Routine:** Set a calendar reminder every 14 days to pull a fresh Search Term Report. Filter for `Spend > $3.00` and `Sales = $0.00`. Any search term meeting this criteria should be evaluated and added to your Negative Keyword Library."
