          "content": "As an expert Advertising Insight Agent, I have analyzed the provided account-wide product performance data for the **MAS-Tools** advertiser account. \n\n### ⚠️ Data Limitation Notice regarding \"Parent ASIN\"\nIn the provided dataset, the `convertedProduct.parentProductId` for all records is returning as `\"-1\"`. Because the true Parent ASINs are not mapped in this data export, I have conducted this product health diagnosis at the **Child ASIN level** (`convertedProduct.id`), which serves as the most accurate proxy for your product-level performance.\n\nHere is the account-wide product health diagnosis based on the top 100 pre-sorted records (Date Range: April 8, 2026 – May 7, 2026).\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Executive Summary\nThe account's recent advertising performance is highly concentrated across two primary ASINs. \n*   **Total Sampled Ad Sales:** ~$32,000+\n*   **Total Sampled Purchases:** ~430+ units\n*   **Dominant Product:** ASIN `B0G13YS92Q` drives the vast majority of volume (~88% of sampled sales).\n\n---\n\n### 🩺 Product Health Diagnosis by ASIN\n\n#### 1. ASIN: B0G13YS92Q (Fanttik - Wheel & Tire Accessories / Pumps)\n*   **Health Status:** 🟢 **Excellent / Hero Product**\n*   **Estimated Sales (Sample):** ~$28,500+ (approx. 375+ purchases)\n*   **Category:** 6000 Wheel & Tire Accessories\n*   **Diagnosis & Insights:**\n    *   **Volume Driver:** This ASIN is the undisputed heavyweight of the account. The campaign *\"Xnurta AI SP-X10 PRO-KW-Brand-Pump\"* alone generated **157 purchases and $11,444.39 in sales**, indicating massive brand loyalty and high conversion rates on branded search terms.\n    *   **Cross-Selling & Halo Effect:** Many campaigns for this ASIN show total `purchases` but `0` `purchasesPromoted` (e.g., *\"Xnurta AI Brand-SP-X9 PRO-KW-Pump\"* with 30 purchases / $2,259 sales). This suggests that ads for other variations or products are successfully driving halo conversions for this specific ASIN.\n    *   **New-To-Brand (NTB) Acquisition:** The campaign *\"Xnurta AI SBV-X10PRO MAX -KW-PH-Pump\"* is a stellar acquisition engine. Out of 11 purchases, **10 were New-To-Brand**, generating $731.90 in NTB sales. Video/SBV formats are highly effective at introducing this product to new customers.\n\n#### 2. ASIN: B0FH6PT5GC (Fanttik - Dusters / Screwdrivers / Polishers)\n*   **Health Status:** 🟡 **Moderate / Growth Opportunity**\n*   **Estimated Sales (Sample):** ~$3,600+ (approx. 53+ purchases)\n*   **Category:** 3000 Desk Organization & Recordkeeping *(Note: Potential catalog miscategorization)*\n*   **Diagnosis & Insights:**\n    *   **B2B Strength:** The top-performing campaign for this ASIN is *\"B2B-B10 PRO MAX-AUTO-duster\"* (13 purchases, $1,013.08 sales). This indicates a strong product-market fit within Amazon Business (B2B) customers.\n    *   **Catalog Warning:** The product is categorized under \"Desk Organization & Recordkeeping,\" but campaign naming conventions (duster, screwdriver, polisher) suggest it is a power tool or cleaning device. This mismatch could be hurting organic indexing and auto-campaign targeting efficiency.\n    *   **Fragmented Campaign Spread:** Sales are spread thinly across many campaigns (mostly 1-3 purchases per campaign). It relies heavily on Auto and ASIN-targeting campaigns rather than high-volume exact match keywords.\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Strategic Recommendations\n\n1.  **Fix Catalog Categorization (Urgent):** \n    Investigate ASIN `B0FH6PT5GC`. If it is indeed a duster or screwdriver, move it out of \"Desk Organization & Recordkeeping\" and into the appropriate Tools/Automotive category. This will immediately improve Auto-campaign relevance and lower CPCs.\n2.  **Scale Video Ads for Acquisition:** \n    ASIN `B0G13YS92Q` has proven that Sponsored Brands Video (SBV) campaigns yield an incredibly high New-To-Brand ratio. Shift more top-of-funnel budget into SBV campaigns targeting generic keywords (e.g., \"tire inflator\", \"portable air pump\") to capture market share.\n3.  **Capitalize on B2B Demand:** \n    ASIN `B0FH6PT5GC` is showing strong B2B traction. Create dedicated B2B-only campaigns with tiered volume discounts (if applicable) and target business-specific keywords to scale this segment.\n4.  **Investigate Parent/Child Tracking:** \n    Work with your Amazon Ads API or reporting setup to ensure `parentProductId` is correctly passing data. Currently, the \"-1\" output prevents true roll-up reporting, which makes it harder to evaluate the health of an entire product family (e.g., the whole \"X10\" or \"X9\" line) at a glance."
