          "content": "# Why These 4 ASINs Had High TACOS in April 2026\n\n**Data Window:** April 1–30, 2026  \n**Source Reports:** Product Conversion Report (8,617 rows) + Campaign Performance Report (1,007 rows)  \n**Account:** MAS-Tools (US marketplace)  \n**Method:** Ad spend per ASIN was attributed proportionally based on each ASIN's share of a campaign's total reported sales.\n\n---\n\n## Account Baseline\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Total Account Ad Spend | $896,917 |\n| Total Account Sales (14-day attribution) | $4,486,556 |\n| Account Average TACOS | **20.0%** |\n| Account Average ACOS | **31.9%** |\n\n---\n\n## TACOS Summary — 4 Target ASINs\n\n| ASIN | Product | Total Sales | Ad Spend (Attributed) | TACOS | ACOS | Promoted Sales % |\n|------|---------|-------------|----------------------|-------|------|-----------------|\n| B0CQYRYKR3 | VAC V9 MIX | $5,787 | $1,053 | **18.2%** | 23.1% | 78.9% |\n| B0DG1KQ9QJ | VAC V10 MIX | $15,255 | $2,990 | **19.6%** | 32.7% | 59.9% |\n| B0D3LSZJK2 | N7PRO Kidscar | $35,434 | $9,447 | **26.7%** | 32.7% | 81.6% |\n| B0DGQ6QJ59 | C8 Nano Scissors | $67,938 | $18,420 | **27.1%** | 30.6% | 88.5% |\n\n**All four ASINs are above (or near) the account average TACOS of 20.0%.** B0D3LSZJK2 and B0DGQ6QJ59 are notably elevated at ~27%.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis by ASIN\n\n### B0DGQ6QJ59 — C8 Nano Scissors (TACOS 27.1%, highest absolute spend $18.4K)\n\n**Primary driver: Extremely high ad dependency — 88.5% of all sales are ad-attributed (promoted sales).**  \nOnly 11.5% of revenue is organic, meaning the product relies almost entirely on paid traffic to convert. The campaign mix reflects aggressive traffic acquisition across multiple high-cost tactics:\n\n| Campaign | Attributed Sales | Attributed Spend | ACOS |\n|----------|-----------------|-----------------|------|\n| SP-C8 Nano Scissors-BO/PH-HL | $14,233 | $4,699 | 33.0% |\n| SP-C8 Nano Scissors-EX主-HL | $11,067 | $3,206 | 29.0% |\n| SP-C8 Nano Scissors-ASIN竞品1-HL | $9,581 | $3,598 | **37.5%** |\n| SB-C8 Nano Scissors-PH/EX-首页 | $8,175 | $1,594 | 19.5% |\n| SP-C8 Nano Scissors-KW-Brand | $6,763 | $892 | 13.2% |\n\n- The competitor ASIN targeting campaign (`ASIN竞品1-HL`) carries 37.5% ACOS — the highest cost efficiency hit.\n- BO/PH (Brand Origination / Product Hunting) and EX (Exact) headline search campaigns are both running at ~29–33% ACOS.\n- The product is new or scaling (brand campaigns at 13% ACOS show there is a loyal buyer base, but non-brand demand requires heavy spend).\n\n**Key insight:** Very low organic ratio (11.5%) combined with broad/competitive placement campaigns drives TACOS to 27%.\n\n---\n\n### B0D3LSZJK2 — N7PRO Kidscar / Wiggle Car (TACOS 26.7%)\n\n**Primary driver: Competitive category requiring high-spend keyword campaigns in the \"wiggle car / kidscar\" segment with elevated CPA.**\n\n| Campaign | Attributed Sales | Attributed Spend | ACOS |\n|----------|-----------------|-----------------|------|\n| SP-KW-N7PRO-Wiggle Car HL-EX | $3,792 | $1,462 | **38.6%** |\n| SP-CAT电动-N7PRO-kidscar | $3,114 | $1,020 | 32.8% |\n| SP-KW-N7PRO-Wiggle Car-BO/PH | $2,634 | $689 | 26.2% |\n| SP-ASIN-N7PRO-竞品同类-kidscar | $2,598 | $1,049 | **40.4%** |\n| SP-KW-N7PRO-次流量词-EX | $1,986 | $599 | 30.2% |\n\n- Competitor ASIN targeting (`竞品同类`) runs at 40.4% ACOS — the worst-performing campaign.\n- \"Wiggle Car\" exact keyword campaigns are running at 38.6% ACOS, suggesting high bid competition for these terms.\n- The product has 81.6% promoted sales dependency — organic ranking has not scaled enough to offset advertising costs.\n- Multiple cross-marketplace campaigns (CA) are also contributing spend, suggesting spending in additional marketplaces.\n\n**Key insight:** Competing in a crowded toy/kids vehicle category forces high bids. Competitor ASIN targeting is particularly inefficient and drags TACOS up.\n\n---\n\n### B0DG1KQ9QJ — VAC V10 MIX (TACOS 19.6%)\n\n**Close to account average; not critically elevated, but notable for a mixed ACOS profile.**\n\n| Campaign | Attributed Sales | Attributed Spend | ACOS |\n|----------|-----------------|-----------------|------|\n| SP-VAC V10 MIX-次大词 | $2,204 | $385 | 17.5% |\n| SP-VAC V10 MIX-闭环+竞对PEER+CAT | $1,988 | $375 | 18.9% |\n| SP-VAC V10 MIX-AUTO | $1,588 | $321 | 20.2% |\n| SP-VAC V10 MIX-大词 Car | $1,049 | $312 | 29.7% |\n\n- This ASIN has the best organic ratio of the four (40.1% of sales are organic), which partially buffers TACOS.\n- Campaign ACOS is concentrated around 18–30%, reasonable for a vacuum product.\n- The \"大词 Car\" (broad vacuum category term) campaign at 29.7% ACOS is the main drag.\n\n**Key insight:** TACOS near account average. The elevated TACOS vs. ideal is mainly from broad category keyword spending with moderate efficiency.\n\n---\n\n### B0CQYRYKR3 — VAC V9 MIX (TACOS 18.2%)\n\n**Just below account average — borderline elevated.**\n\n| Campaign | Attributed Sales | Attributed Spend | ACOS |\n|----------|-----------------|-----------------|------|\n| SP-VAC V9 MIX-闭环 | $2,179 | $375 | 17.2% |\n| SP-VAC V9 MIX-AUTO | $1,328 | $238 | 17.9% |\n| SP-VAC V9 MIX-PH-低价大词 | $176 | $62 | **35.3%** |\n\n- Most campaigns are efficient (17–18% ACOS) but the broad \"低价大词 car vacuum\" campaign has 35.3% ACOS on low volume.\n- Ad dependency is high at 78.9% promoted sales.\n- Total sales volume ($5.8K) is low — this is a smaller product contributing low absolute spend.\n\n**Key insight:** TACOS is acceptable but elevated from limited organic traffic and one inefficient broad keyword campaign.\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Why TACOS Is High\n\n| Root Cause | B0CQYRYKR3 | B0DG1KQ9QJ | B0DGQ6QJ59 | B0D3LSZJK2 |\n|-----------|:---------:|:---------:|:---------:|:---------:|\n| High ad dependency (low organic %) | ✓ | — | ✓✓ | ✓✓ |\n| Inefficient competitor ASIN targeting | — | — | ✓ | ✓✓ |\n| High-cost broad/category keywords | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |\n| Competitive category (high CPCs) | — | — | ✓ | ✓✓ |\n| Multiple marketplace campaigns (CA) | — | — | — | ✓ |\n\n**The two most elevated ASINs (B0DGQ6QJ59 and B0D3LSZJK2) share the same core problem: very low organic sales ratios combined with aggressive competitor targeting campaigns running at 37–40% ACOS.** For the C8 Scissors, this is a new/scaling product relying entirely on paid traffic. For the N7PRO Kidscar, it is a highly competitive keyword category where bids are inflated by direct competitor targeting.\n\n**Recommendations:**\n1. **B0DGQ6QJ59 / B0D3LSZJK2:** Reduce or pause competitor ASIN targeting campaigns (37–40% ACOS) — these have the worst efficiency. Shift budget to brand and own-ASIN retargeting (13–20% ACOS range).\n2. **B0DGQ6QJ59:** Improve organic rank to reduce 88.5% ad dependency — review listing optimization and pricing relative to organic conversion rate.\n3. **B0D3LSZJK2:** Audit \"Wiggle Car\" exact keyword bids — 38.6% ACOS suggests overbidding. Test lower bids or switch to dynamic down-only.\n4. **All 4 ASINs:** The account average ACOS is 31.9% vs 20% TACOS, which suggests healthy organic contribution overall — but these ASINs need to grow their organic ratio to bring TACOS down sustainably.\n"
