          "label": "Sonnet 4.5",
          "content": "# EV088: SP/SD/SB Campaign Analysis for 3 ASINs\n\n## Data Limitation\n\nThe current dataset provides aggregate performance across all campaign types but lacks breakdown by SP (Sponsored Products), SD (Sponsored Display), and SB (Sponsored Brands). Analysis will focus on overall performance with campaign-type-specific recommendations based on typical use cases.\n\n## Performance Comparison\n\n| ASIN | Ad Spend | Sales | Orders | ACOS | CVR | CPC | ROAS | Status |\n|------|----------|-------|--------|------|-----|-----|------|--------|\n| B0DN1GBTDG | $41,631 | $199,352 | 2,902 | 20.9% | 9.6% | $1.38 | 4.79 | ⚠️ Scale Opportunity |\n| B0D41ZMDPD | $23,217 | $121,693 | 2,000 | 19.1% | 12.3% | $1.42 | 5.24 | ✅ Healthy |\n| B0DGQ6QJ59 | $20,152 | $71,930 | 1,401 | 28.0% | 20.5% | $2.95 | 3.57 | 🔴 Needs Optimization |\n\n## Individual ASIN Analysis\n\n### B0DN1GBTDG - Scale Opportunity\n**Performance**: Highest revenue ($199K) but moderate efficiency\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Highest sales volume and order count\n- Moderate ACOS (20.9%) - acceptable\n- Reasonable CPC ($1.38)\n- High impression volume (3.09M)\n\n**Weaknesses:**\n- **Low CVR (9.6%)** - conversion efficiency below optimal\n- High spend with room for efficiency improvement\n\n**Optimization Priority**: Improve conversion rate while scaling\n\n### B0D41ZMDPD - Healthy Performer\n**Performance**: Best balanced metrics\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Good ACOS (19.1%) - most efficient\n- Strong CVR (12.3%) - good conversion\n- Best ROAS (5.24)\n- Reasonable CPC ($1.42)\n\n**Weaknesses:**\n- Moderate spend - could scale further\n- CTR (0.77%) could be improved\n\n**Optimization Priority**: Scale investment while maintaining efficiency\n\n### B0DGQ6QJ59 - Critical Issues\n**Performance**: Inefficient, needs immediate attention\n\n**Strengths:**\n- **Excellent CVR (20.5%)** - highest conversion rate\n- Good order volume (1,401)\n\n**Weaknesses:**\n- **High ACOS (28.0%)** - unprofitable at this level\n- **Extremely high CPC ($2.95)** - overpaying for clicks\n- Low ROAS (3.57) - poor return\n- Lowest CTR (0.89%) despite high CPC\n\n**Optimization Priority**: Reduce costs urgently\n\n## Campaign-Type-Specific Recommendations\n\n### Sponsored Products (SP) Recommendations\n\n**B0DN1GBTDG (Low CVR Issue)**\n1. **Listing Optimization**:\n   - Improve main image and A+ content to boost 9.6% CVR\n   - Add/update product videos\n   - Optimize bullet points for conversion\n2. **Keyword Strategy**:\n   - Focus on high-intent keywords (CVR >12%)\n   - Add negative keywords to filter low-quality traffic\n   - Test Exact match for proven converters\n3. **Bid Strategy**:\n   - Maintain current CPC ($1.38) - it's working\n   - Increase bids on high-CVR keywords only\n\n**B0D41ZMDPD (Scale Opportunity)**\n1. **Budget Expansion**:\n   - Increase daily budget by 30-40%\n   - Expand to additional high-volume keywords\n2. **Match Type Expansion**:\n   - Add Phrase match for proven Exact keywords\n   - Test Broad match with close monitoring\n3. **Placement Optimization**:\n   - Increase top-of-search bids (strong CVR supports it)\n\n**B0DGQ6QJ59 (Cost Reduction)**\n1. **Immediate Bid Reduction**:\n   - Reduce bids by 30-40% to lower CPC from $2.95\n   - Target CPC: $1.80-2.00\n2. **Keyword Audit**:\n   - Identify expensive keywords (CPC >$3)\n   - Pause or drastically reduce bids on low-ROAS terms\n3. **Placement Strategy**:\n   - Reduce top-of-search modifier (likely driving high CPC)\n   - Test product pages and rest-of-search placements\n\n### Sponsored Display (SD) Recommendations\n\n**B0DN1GBTDG**\n- **Audience Targeting**: Use \"Views Remarketing\" to retarget visitors (boost 9.6% CVR)\n- **Product Targeting**: Target competitor ASINs with similar products\n- **Budget**: Allocate 15-20% of total ad budget to SD\n\n**B0D41ZMDPD**\n- **Remarketing**: Capture lost visitors with SD remarketing\n- **Lookalike Audiences**: Expand reach to similar shoppers\n- **Budget**: Allocate 10-15% of budget (already efficient)\n\n**B0DGQ6QJ59**\n- **Pause SD temporarily** until ACOS improves\n- SD typically has higher CPM - not suitable for current high-cost situation\n- Resume after SP optimization brings ACOS below 22%\n\n### Sponsored Brands (SB) Recommendations\n\n**B0DN1GBTDG**\n- **Brand Awareness**: Launch SB for category keywords\n- **Video Ads**: Use SB Video to showcase product features (help CVR)\n- **Budget**: 10-15% of total budget\n- **Keywords**: Broad category terms (e.g., \"wireless charger\", \"phone accessories\")\n\n**B0D41ZMDPD**\n- **Competitive Conquesting**: Target competitor brand terms\n- **Store Spotlight**: Drive traffic to brand store\n- **Budget**: 10% of total budget\n- **Strategy**: Focus on high-volume, mid-funnel keywords\n\n**B0DGQ6QJ59**\n- **Pause SB campaigns** until efficiency improves\n- SB typically has lower CVR than SP - not suitable now\n- Focus all budget on SP optimization first\n\n## Optimization Priority Matrix\n\n### Immediate Actions (Week 1)\n\n**B0DGQ6QJ59 - URGENT**\n1. Reduce all bids by 35%\n2. Pause keywords with CPC >$3.50\n3. Reduce top-of-search placement modifier to 0%\n4. Target: Bring ACOS from 28% to 22%\n\n**B0DN1GBTDG - HIGH**\n1. Optimize listing (images, A+, video)\n2. Add 50+ negative keywords\n3. Launch SD remarketing campaign\n4. Target: Improve CVR from 9.6% to 11%\n\n**B0D41ZMDPD - MEDIUM**\n1. Increase daily budget by 30%\n2. Expand keyword targeting (add 20 new keywords)\n3. Launch SB campaign for brand awareness\n4. Target: Increase sales by 25% while maintaining 19% ACOS\n\n### Short-Term Goals (Month 1)\n\n| ASIN | Current ACOS | Target ACOS | Current Sales | Target Sales | Strategy |\n|------|--------------|-------------|---------------|--------------|----------|\n| B0DGQ6QJ59 | 28.0% | 22.0% | $71,930 | $65,000 | Cost reduction (accept sales dip) |\n| B0DN1GBTDG | 20.9% | 19.0% | $199,352 | $230,000 | Efficiency + scale |\n| B0D41ZMDPD | 19.1% | 18.0% | $121,693 | $155,000 | Scale while optimizing |\n\n### Campaign Budget Allocation Recommendation\n\n**B0DN1GBTDG** (Total: $45K/month)\n- SP: 70% ($31.5K) - Primary driver\n- SD: 20% ($9K) - Remarketing\n- SB: 10% ($4.5K) - Brand awareness\n\n**B0D41ZMDPD** (Total: $30K/month)\n- SP: 75% ($22.5K) - Primary driver\n- SD: 15% ($4.5K) - Remarketing\n- SB: 10% ($3K) - Competitive\n\n**B0DGQ6QJ59** (Total: $15K/month - reduced from $20K)\n- SP: 100% ($15K) - Focus on efficiency\n- SD: 0% - Paused\n- SB: 0% - Paused\n\n## Expected Results (30 Days)\n\n**Overall Account Impact:**\n- Total Spend: Reduce from $85K to $90K (slight increase for scaling)\n- Total Sales: Increase from $393K to $450K (+15%)\n- Overall ACOS: Improve from 21.6% to 19.5%\n- Total Orders: Increase from 6,303 to 7,200 (+14%)\n\n**By ASIN:**\n- **B0DGQ6QJ59**: ACOS 28% → 22%, Sales stable or slight decline (acceptable tradeoff)\n- **B0DN1GBTDG**: ACOS 20.9% → 19%, Sales +15% through CVR improvement\n- **B0D41ZMDPD**: ACOS 19.1% → 18%, Sales +25% through scaling\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. **Week 1**: Implement urgent B0DGQ6QJ59 cost reductions\n2. **Week 2**: Launch SD remarketing for B0DN1GBTDG and B0D41ZMDPD\n3. **Week 3**: Optimize B0DN1GBTDG listing and monitor CVR improvement\n4. **Week 4**: Scale B0D41ZMDPD budget and launch SB campaigns\n5. **Day 30**: Review results and adjust strategy for Month 2\n"
