          "label": "Gemini 3.1 Pro",
          "content": "Based on the provided pre-processed data (spanning April 8, 2025, to May 7, 2025), I have analyzed the Sponsored Products (SP), Sponsored Brands (SB), and Sponsored Display (SD) campaigns. \n\n*Note: The provided data uses internal product naming conventions rather than raw ASINs. Based on the campaign nomenclature, I have mapped your three requested ASINs (B0DN1GBTDG, B0DGQ6QJ59, B0D41ZMDPD) to the three distinct product lines present in the data: **F2 Master RT (Rotary Tool)**, **C8 Nano Scissors**, and **T1 MAX (Solder)**.*\n\nHere is the comprehensive analysis and optimization strategy for your campaigns.\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Executive Summary & Macro Trends\nAcross all three product lines, a clear pattern emerges:\n1. **Brand & Remarketing Dominance:** Brand keyword campaigns (SP) and Remarketing/Similar Audience campaigns (SD) are delivering exceptionally high returns (ROAS ranging from 10x to 34x).\n2. **AMC Audience Struggles:** Campaigns utilizing AMC (Amazon Marketing Cloud) custom audiences (e.g., \"已购买相似\" - purchased similar) are generally underperforming in SP, yielding ROAS below 1.0 in some cases.\n3. **B2B Variability:** B2B targeting shows mixed results. It is highly efficient in SB video formats but struggles with low conversion rates in SP Auto campaigns.\n\n---\n\n### 🛠️ 1. Product Line: F2 Master RT (Rotary Tool)\n\n**Performance Analysis:**\n*   **SP (Sponsored Products):** Volume is massive. The `AUTO-HL` and `ASIN竞品-HL` (Competitor ASIN) campaigns are the primary sales drivers, generating ~$31k and ~$29k in sales respectively, with healthy ROAS (4.81 and 5.71). However, the `EX-Rotary Tool-HL` (Exact match) campaign is bleeding efficiency (ROAS 1.60).\n*   **SD (Sponsored Display):** Performance is outstanding. The `Similar-VCPM` campaign achieved a staggering **34.52 ROAS**, and the `Remarketing-AP` campaign hit **15.59 ROAS** with over $16k in sales.\n\n**Optimization Recommendations:**\n*   **Scale SD Aggressively:** Uncap budgets for `SD-F2 Master RT-Similar-VCPM` and `SD-F2 Master RT-Remarketing-AP`. These are your most efficient conversion engines.\n*   **Trim SP Inefficiencies:** Drastically reduce bids or pause the `SP-F2 Master RT-EX-Rotary Tool-HL` campaign. Reallocate this budget to the high-performing `CAT-RotaryTool-HL` (ROAS 5.74, low CPC of $0.80).\n*   **Maintain Top-of-Search:** Keep funding the high-volume Auto and Competitor ASIN SP campaigns, but implement day-parting or slight bid shading to push their ROAS above 6.0.\n\n---\n\n### ✂️ 2. Product Line: C8 Nano Scissors\n\n**Performance Analysis:**\n*   **SP (Sponsored Products):** Brand defense is incredibly strong (`KW-Brand` ROAS is 24.74). However, exploratory campaigns are failing. The `AUTO-AMC-已购买相似` campaign has a dismal ROAS of 0.85, and the `B2B-AUTO` campaign is sitting at 2.04 ROAS.\n*   **SB (Sponsored Brands):** The main horizontal video campaign (`KW-横版-多卖点-CPC`) is driving good volume ($3.1k sales, 3.70 ROAS). Conversely, competitor targeting in SB (`ASIN竞品-横版`) is inefficient (1.89 ROAS).\n*   **SD (Sponsored Display):** Consistent with the F2 Master, SD is highly profitable. `Remarketing-AP` (10.46 ROAS) and `Similar-VCPM` (13.42 ROAS) are performing beautifully.\n\n**Optimization Recommendations:**\n*   **Pause AMC & B2B Auto:** Immediately pause `SP-C8 Nano Scissors-AUTO-AMC` and `B2B-C8 NANO-AUTO`. The traffic intent does not align with conversions for this product.\n*   **Refine SB Strategy:** Shift budget away from SB Competitor ASINs and the \"Purchased Similar\" SB campaigns. Funnel those dollars into the main `SBV-C8 Nano Scissors-KW-横版` campaign, which is successfully acquiring New-to-Brand customers (42 NTB purchases).\n*   **Maximize SD:** Increase the vCPM bids slightly on the `SDV-C8 Nano Scissors-Similar-VCPM` to win more high-quality impressions, as the current CPC equivalent is very cheap ($0.95).\n\n---\n\n### ⚡ 3. Product Line: T1 MAX (Solder)\n\n**Performance Analysis:**\n*   **SP (Sponsored Products):** The `KW-A-solder` campaign is the heavy lifter ($20k sales, 5.21 ROAS). Brand keywords are excellent (10.81 ROAS). However, the `ASIN-必胜竞品` (Must-win competitor) campaign is struggling at 2.71 ROAS, and the AMC keyword campaign generated 0 sales.\n*   **SB (Sponsored Brands):** We see a stark contrast in ad formats. The vertical video (`SBV-T1 MAX-KW-竖版`) spent money with 0 sales. Meanwhile, the **B2B SBV campaign** (`B2B-Xmars AI SBV-T1 MAX-KW-横板`) is a hidden gem with a **17.13 ROAS**.\n*   **SD (Sponsored Display):** Competitor targeting works much better in SD than SP for this product. The `SD-T1 MAX-ASIN-VCPM-competitors` campaign boasts a 14.48 ROAS.\n\n**Optimization Recommendations:**\n*   **Kill the Vertical Video:** Pause `SBV-T1 MAX-KW-竖版-无绳...` immediately. The format or creative is not resonating with the soldering audience.\n*   **Capitalize on B2B Video:** The B2B audience responds incredibly well to the horizontal video highlighting \"7S fast heating/cordless\". Significantly increase the budget for `B2B-Xmars AI SBV-T1 MAX-KW-横板`.\n*   **Shift Competitor Strategy:** Since SP competitor targeting (`ASIN-必胜竞品`) is underperforming (2.71 ROAS) but SD competitor targeting is thriving (14.48 ROAS), move your aggressive competitor conquesting budget from SP to SD. \n\n---\n\n### 🚀 Next Steps for the Account Manager\n1. **Audit AMC Audiences:** The custom AMC audiences built for \"Purchased Similar\" are currently wasting spend across SP and SB. Re-evaluate the lookback windows or overlap criteria in the AMC console before re-enabling.\n2. **Consolidate SD Budgets:** Across all three ASINs, Sponsored Display (specifically Remarketing and Similar Audiences via vCPM) is your highest-margin channel. Ensure these campaigns never run out of budget during peak shopping hours."
