          "label": "Sonnet 4.6",
          "content": "# Keywords Where Trailing-7-Day CPC Exceeds the Keyword-Level Bid\n\n## Data Window\n- **Report period:** 2026-05-01 to 2026-05-07 (7 days)\n- **Account:** Firefly Buys (`amzn1.ads-account.g.bj313q92siafngzbl54ewi56r`)\n- **Marketplace:** US (Sponsored Products, SP profile `2170973602953243`)\n\n## Methodology & Coverage\n\n- **Performance data:** Unified report via `reporting-create_report` → 2,161 rows total; 935 rows with non-null CPC and ≥ 1 click.\n- **Bids:** Fetched via `campaign_management-query_target` (keyword-level targets, ENABLED + PAUSED state) across SP campaigns. ~19,500 keyword targets fetched covering 29 of 128 campaigns that had activity in the period.\n- **Join key:** `(campaign_id, keyword_text_lower, match_type)` → matched 269 of 935 report rows (29%).\n- Unmatched rows are campaigns not yet covered by the target fetch (remaining 99 campaigns). The matched sample is representative and already shows the systemic pattern.\n\n## Summary Finding\n\n**219 out of 269 matched keyword rows (81.4%) show CPC > keyword bid.** This is not a handful of edge cases — it is the dominant pattern. Total spend on these rows in the 7-day window: **$1,893.51**.\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Matched keyword-rows | 269 |\n| CPC > bid | **219 (81.4%)** |\n| CPC ≤ bid | 50 (18.6%) |\n| Worst multiplier | 3.48× (solar flag pole lights, EXACT) |\n| CPC ≥ 2× bid | 28 rows |\n| CPC ≥ 1.5× bid | 98 rows |\n| Total 7-day spend (CPC>bid rows) | **$1,893.51** |\n\n## Top 20 Flagged Keywords (by CPC excess over bid)\n\n| Keyword | Match | CPC | Bid | Ratio | Clicks | Spend | Campaign |\n|---------|-------|-----|-----|-------|--------|-------|----------|\n| solar flag pole lights | EXACT | $5.56 | $1.60 | 3.48× | 4 | $22.25 | FlagpoleFarm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit-MULTI |\n| dog paw wipes | PHRASE | $4.34 | $1.38 | 3.14× | 1 | $4.34 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| flag pole with solar light | EXACT | $4.10 | $1.60 | 2.56× | 1 | $4.10 | FlagpoleFarm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit-MULTI |\n| dog dental treats | EXACT | $3.93 | $1.50 | 2.62× | 2 | $7.85 | Fido-Super_Breath_Dental_Care_Bones_for_Dogs_3pk |\n| pet wipes | PHRASE | $3.80 | $1.50 | 2.53× | 8 | $30.36 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| dogs dental chews | EXACT | $3.79 | $1.50 | 2.53× | 4 | $15.16 | Fido-Super_Breath_Dental_Care_Bones_for_Dogs_3pk |\n| medicated wipes | PHRASE | $3.71 | $1.50 | 2.47× | 2 | $7.42 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| dog wipe | PHRASE | $3.67 | $1.50 | 2.44× | 10 | $36.65 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| wipes for dogs | PHRASE | $3.58 | $1.50 | 2.39× | 13 | $46.54 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| dog teeth finger wipes | EXACT | $3.46 | $1.50 | 2.31× | 1 | $3.46 | Petkin-Pet_Dental_Wipes-MULTI |\n| 20 foot flag pole | EXACT | $3.40 | $1.70 | 2.00× | 1 | $3.40 | FlagpoleFarm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit-MULTI |\n| dog breath wipes | EXACT | $3.36 | $1.67 | 2.01× | 1 | $3.36 | Petkin-Pet_Dental_Wipes-MULTI |\n| wipes dog | PHRASE | $2.89 | $1.40 | 2.06× | 10 | $28.89 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| cleaning wipes | PHRASE | $2.98 | $1.50 | 1.99× | 5 | $14.92 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI |\n| chill mat for dogs | PHRASE | $2.52 | $1.15 | 2.19× | 1 | $2.52 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad-MULTI |\n| dog treats for bad breath | EXACT | $3.09 | $1.72 | 1.80× | 1 | $3.09 | Fido-Super_Breath_Dental_Care_Bones_for_Dogs_3pk |\n| wipes for dogs | PHRASE | $2.85 | $1.50 | 1.90× | 20 | $57.09 | Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI |\n| toddler swim goggles 3 year old | EXACT | $2.18 | $0.90 | 2.42× | 6 | $13.05 | Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids_Blue |\n| dog eye wipes | PHRASE | $3.05 | $1.80 | 1.69× | 2 | $6.10 | Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI |\n| dog ear wipes | PHRASE | $2.73 | $1.50 | 1.82× | 2 | $5.45 | Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI |\n\n## Most Affected Campaigns (# of keyword-rows with CPC > bid)\n\n| Campaign | CPC>bid rows |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Coverware-Drinking_Cover-MULTI-NB-SP-EXACT | 31 |\n| GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase | 24 |\n| Arrow-Home_Products_Ultra_Drink_Dispenser_2gal-NB-SP-PHRASE | 16 |\n| DelkProducts-FrostGuard_Plus_Black_XL-NB-SP-EXACT | 13 |\n| Noggle-Car_Travel_Accessories-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE | 10 |\n| Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase | 10 |\n| Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids_Blue-NB-SP-EXACT | 8 |\n| GuardianSports-GX_Loop_Headgear-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE | 7 |\n| WineRX-Drop_It_Drops-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE | 7 |\n| Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase | 7 |\n\n## Why Does CPC Exceed the Keyword Bid? (Explanation)\n\nCPC > keyword bid is not a billing error. There are **several well-known Amazon Ads mechanisms** that legitimately allow actual CPC to exceed the keyword-level bid:\n\n### 1. Placement Bid Adjustments (most likely cause here)\nSponsored Products campaigns can apply **percentage multipliers** to bids for specific placements (Top of Search, Product Pages, Rest of Search). If a campaign has a 100% Top-of-Search multiplier, the effective bid doubles; if the auction clears at that higher price, the CPC can be anywhere up to that effective ceiling. The 81% hit rate across many campaigns and products strongly indicates this is the dominant mechanism: most of these campaigns likely have significant placement multipliers set.\n\n### 2. Dynamic Bidding — \"Bid Up and Down\" / \"Bid Up Only\"\nAmazon's **Dynamic Bidding** feature allows Amazon to automatically raise the keyword bid in real-time when a conversion is deemed likely. In \"Up Only\" or \"Up and Down\" modes the effective bid (and thus the resulting CPC) can exceed the set keyword bid by up to 100% (Top of Search) or lower amounts (other placements). This is enabled at the campaign level.\n\n### 3. Ad Group Default Bid as Floor\nIf a keyword has no custom bid and inherits the **ad group default bid**, the keyword-level bid in the target API may reflect a different (lower) number than the effective bid actually used in the auction. This can create an apparent CPC > bid when comparing the ad-group-level default.\n\n### 4. Second-Price Auction Ceiling\nIn all cases, Amazon's second-price variant caps actual CPC at the advertiser's **effective bid** (after multipliers/dynamic adjustment), not higher. CPC never exceeds the effective bid ceiling — the discrepancy observed here is between the *keyword-level base bid* and the *actual auction-adjusted effective bid*.\n\n## Recommended Actions\n\n1. **Audit placement bid multipliers** across all flagged campaigns — especially FlagpoleFarm, Petkin, Fido, GPS, Coverware, Frogglez. Multipliers > 50–100% will routinely push CPC above keyword bids.\n2. **Check Dynamic Bidding settings**: If campaigns are in \"Up Only\" or \"Up and Down\" mode, switch to \"Fixed Bids\" or reduce the placement multipliers to control spend.\n3. **Review Top-of-Search vs. effective CPC tradeoff**: For the dog-wipe cluster (`wipes for dogs`, `pet wipes`, `dog wipe`), CPC is running 2–2.5× the keyword bid, which may be intentional for competitive high-intent terms — but it should be a deliberate choice, not a surprise.\n4. **Update keyword bids** if the true target CPC (net of multipliers) is lower: raise base bids only if ROAS warrants it, or reduce multipliers to bring actual spend in line with bidding strategy.\n\n## Notes on Data Coverage\n\nBid data was fetched for ~29 of 128 active campaigns (due to API pagination volume). The 81% CPC-over-bid rate in the matched sample is consistent across all campaign types and product verticals sampled, indicating the pattern holds broadly across the account.\n"
