          "label": "Opus 4.7",
          "content": "# Keywords Where Trailing-7-Day CPC Exceeds the Keyword-Level Bid\n\n## Data window & scope\n- Window: **2026-05-01 → 2026-05-07 (trailing 7 days)**.\n- Sources: keyword performance report × target-ad-entity table (the keyword's currently-set bid).\n- Keywords flagged: **219** where `CPC > bid`.\n\n## How can this even happen?\nUnder normal Amazon bidding mechanics, CPC should never exceed a keyword's standing bid: the auction is second-price, so you pay at most the second-highest bid (which is ≤ your bid). If realized CPC > bid, one of these things is true:\n\n1. **Bid was recently lowered** within the 7-day window — earlier clicks at the old (higher) bid still count in the CPC denominator.\n2. **Top-of-search or product-page bid modifier** is adding a premium (e.g., TOS +100% on a $1.60 base bid effectively makes the auction bid $3.20).\n3. **Dynamic-bid \"up-and-down\" strategy** is raising the bid above the standing keyword bid in high-intent auctions.\n4. **Placement- or audience-level boost** (e.g., Xnurta AI's AMC audience boost) adding a multiplier.\n5. **Campaign-level bid adjustments** applied on top of keyword bid.\n6. **Clock-skew / reporting lag** — the bid shown is the current value; the CPC is the 7-day average. Rare mismatches can exceed 2× for 1–2 clicks.\n\n## Match type distribution\n\n| Match | Flagged |\n|---|---:|\n| PHRASE | 127 |\n| EXACT | 92 |\n\nClicks on each row are mostly small (68 rows have just 1 click; most flags have ≤ 5 clicks). The ratio = CPC/bid is the interesting number.\n\n## Top 15 flagged rows (highest ratio = CPC/bid)\n\n| Keyword | Match | CPC | Bid | Ratio | Excess $ | Clicks | Impressions | Campaign (trunc.) |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| solar flag pole lights | EXACT | $5.56 | $1.60 | **3.48x** | $3.96 | 4 | 303 | FlagpoleFarm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit SP Exact |\n| dog paw wipes | PHRASE | $4.34 | $1.38 | 3.14x | $2.96 | 1 | 157 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large SP Phrase |\n| noggle | PHRASE | $0.59 | $0.20 | 2.97x | $0.39 | 76 | 2,376 | Noggle-Car_Travel_Accessories Branded SP Phrase |\n| noggles | PHRASE | $0.57 | $0.20 | 2.87x | $0.38 | 12 | 192 | Noggle-Car_Travel_Accessories Branded SP Phrase |\n| dog dental treats | EXACT | $3.92 | $1.50 | 2.62x | $2.42 | 2 | 3,165 | Fido-Super_Breath_Dental_Care SP |\n| flag pole with solar light | EXACT | $4.10 | $1.60 | 2.56x | $2.50 | 1 | 105 | FlagpoleFarm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit SP Exact |\n| pet wipes | PHRASE | $3.79 | $1.50 | 2.53x | $2.29 | 8 | 330 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large SP Phrase |\n| dogs dental chews | EXACT | $3.79 | $1.50 | 2.53x | $2.29 | 4 | 5,172 | Fido-Super_Breath_Dental_Care SP |\n| medicated wipes | PHRASE | $3.71 | $1.50 | 2.47x | $2.21 | 2 | 55 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large SP Phrase |\n| dog wipe | PHRASE | $3.67 | $1.50 | 2.44x | $2.17 | 10 | 1,044 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large SP Phrase |\n| bpa free plastic plates | PHRASE | $0.73 | $0.30 | 2.43x | $0.43 | 1 | 133 | Arrow-Home_Products_Fiesta_Taco_Plate SP |\n| toddler swim goggles 3 year old | EXACT | $2.17 | $0.90 | 2.42x | $1.27 | 6 | 3,666 | Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids_Blue SP Exact |\n| dog gel mat | PHRASE | $1.21 | $0.50 | 2.41x | $0.70 | 2 | 12 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad SP Phrase |\n| wipes for dogs | PHRASE | $3.58 | $1.50 | 2.39x | $2.08 | 13 | 886 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large SP Phrase |\n| drink tops by coverware | EXACT | $0.47 | $0.20 | 2.33x | $0.27 | 2 | 70 | Coverware-CatchAll Branded SP Exact |\n\n## Patterns\n\n### FlagpoleFarm Titan campaign (solar flag pole lights, flag pole with solar light)\nBoth flagged keywords in this campaign have bid $1.60 but CPC $4.10–$5.56. **Almost certainly a top-of-search bid modifier** set at +200% or higher combined with Dynamic Up-and-Down strategy. Verify the campaign's placement bid adjustments.\n\n### Petkin BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large campaign (6 flagged keywords at bid $1.50, CPC $3.50–$4.34)\nThe uniform bid of $1.50 across multiple keywords with CPC consistently landing at 2–3× suggests a single campaign-level adjustment affecting all of them. Likely: TOS modifier at +150–200%, or a bidding strategy change (\"Dynamic up-and-down\" with aggressive multiplier).\n\n### Noggle Branded (noggle, noggles at bid $0.20, CPC $0.57–$0.59)\nLow base bid + AMC audience boost (common for Xnurta AI Branded SP) explains the 2.87–2.97× ratio. AMC audience boost can add 200–300% on top of base bid for high-intent users.\n\n### Fido dental-treats keywords\nBid $1.50, CPC $3.79–$3.92. Same pattern as Petkin: uniform-bid campaign with aggressive placement modifiers.\n\n## Recommended actions\n\n### 1. Verify placement bid adjustments on flagged campaigns\nFor each of the top 5 campaigns in the flag list (FlagpoleFarm, Petkin, Fido, Frogglez, Coverware), export the placement bid modifiers. If TOS is > +100%, that's the explanation — either keep it intentional (high-value top-of-search) or reduce it to bring CPC closer to bid.\n\n### 2. Either raise the bid or lower the modifier\n- If the TOS modifier is *deliberate* and the keyword is converting: raise the base bid so CPC is closer to a \"real\" set value. Keyword at $1.50 bid with TOS +150% means effective bid $3.75 — just set it to $3.75 directly.\n- If the TOS modifier is *default-high without calibration*: drop it to +50% and let the keyword's natural bid do its work.\n\n### 3. Monitor AMC audience boost on branded campaigns\nThe `noggle` PHRASE flag shows the classic pattern: low brand-bid + aggressive audience multiplier. Branded keywords don't typically need audience boost — the searcher is already high-intent. Consider dropping the AMC multiplier on Noggle Branded campaigns.\n\n### 4. Address flags with low clicks only if consistent\nKeywords with 1–2 clicks and high ratio (like `solar flag pole lights` at 4 clicks) are single-auction anomalies. Watch for a second week of the same pattern before acting.\n\n## Summary of flagged excess spend (combined)\nTotal excess dollars (CPC − bid) × clicks = **~$220 across 7 days = ~$940/mo annualized**. Not an enormous dollar amount by itself, but the placement-modifier issue behind it likely affects many non-flagged keywords too.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Placement-level bid modifier** snapshot for each flagged campaign (the critical input to explain each flag).\n- **Keyword bid changelog** — to rule in/out \"bid was just lowered\".\n- **Bid strategy per campaign** (Dynamic up-and-down vs. Fixed vs. Dynamic down only).\n- **AMC / audience-boost multipliers** for branded campaigns.\n- **Historical 7-day window** to see if these flags are chronic or one-off.\n"
