          "content": "# EV155: 13-Week ACOS Trend Analysis\n\n## Weekly ACOS Data (Feb 6 - May 7, 2026)\n\n| Week | Dates | Spend | Sales | ACOS | ROAS | Orders |\n|------|-------|-------|-------|------|------|--------|\n| 1 | Feb 6-12 | $7,379 | $36,646 | **20.1%** | 4.97 | 924 |\n| 2 | Feb 13-19 | $8,484 | $43,438 | **19.5%** | 5.12 | 1,101 |\n| 3 | Feb 20-26 | $9,118 | $53,758 | **17.0%** | 5.90 | 1,097 |\n| 4 | Feb 27-Mar 5 | $5,777 | $34,025 | **17.0%** | 5.89 | 814 |\n| 5 | Mar 6-12 | $7,619 | $43,714 | **17.4%** | 5.74 | 1,215 |\n| 6 | Mar 13-19 | $6,326 | $38,765 | **16.3%** | 6.13 | 1,117 |\n| 7 | Mar 20-26 | $6,646 | $42,430 | **15.7%** | 6.38 | 1,233 |\n| 8 | Mar 27-Apr 2 | $6,272 | $42,801 | **14.7%** ⭐ | 6.82 | 1,108 |\n| 9 | Apr 3-9 | $8,264 | $46,279 | **17.9%** | 5.60 | 1,115 |\n| 10 | Apr 10-16 | $14,018 | $72,157 | **19.4%** | 5.15 | 1,633 |\n| 11 | Apr 17-23 | $12,792 | $64,436 | **19.9%** | 5.04 | 1,320 |\n| 12 | Apr 24-30 | $10,567 | $54,780 | **19.3%** | 5.18 | 1,048 |\n| 13 | May 1-7 | $11,858 | $56,195 | **21.1%** 🔴 | 4.74 | 1,130 |\n\n## Trend Analysis\n\n### Clear Upward Trend in ACOS\n\n**Phase 1: Weeks 1-4 (February)**\n- Average ACOS: **18.4%**\n- Range: 17.0% - 20.1%\n- Status: Moderate efficiency\n\n**Phase 2: Weeks 5-8 (March)**\n- Average ACOS: **16.0%**\n- Range: 14.7% - 17.4%\n- Status: **Best performance period** ⭐\n- Week 8 achieved lowest ACOS: 14.7%\n\n**Phase 3: Weeks 9-13 (April-May)**\n- Average ACOS: **19.9%**\n- Range: 17.9% - 21.1%\n- Status: **Deteriorating efficiency** 🔴\n- Week 13 hit highest ACOS: 21.1%\n\n### Statistical Analysis\n\n**Trend Direction**: ⬆️ **Upward (Worsening)**\n\n**Key Metrics:**\n- **Best week**: Week 8 (Mar 27-Apr 2) - 14.7% ACOS\n- **Worst week**: Week 13 (May 1-7) - 21.1% ACOS\n- **Total variance**: 6.4 percentage points\n- **Recent trend**: +5.1% increase from best to worst\n\n**Comparison:**\n- First 4 weeks avg: 18.4%\n- Last 4 weeks avg: 19.9%\n- **Change**: +1.5 percentage points (+8.2% increase)\n\n## Verdict: TREND, Not Noise\n\n### Evidence of Real Trend\n\n**1. Consistent Pattern**\n- March (weeks 5-8): Consistently low ACOS (14.7-17.4%)\n- April-May (weeks 9-13): Consistently high ACOS (17.9-21.1%)\n- Clear phase separation\n\n**2. Magnitude of Change**\n- 6.4 percentage point swing is significant\n- 8.2% increase in recent 4 weeks vs. first 4 weeks\n- Too large to be random noise\n\n**3. Directional Consistency**\n- March: Improving trend (peaked at 14.7%)\n- April-May: Deteriorating trend (reached 21.1%)\n- Not random fluctuation\n\n**4. Spend Correlation**\n- Week 10 (highest spend $14K): ACOS jumped to 19.4%\n- Weeks 11-13 (high spend): ACOS remained elevated\n- Suggests spend increase drove ACOS up\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n### Why ACOS Increased in April-May\n\n**1. Increased Spend Without Proportional Sales**\n| Period | Avg Weekly Spend | Avg Weekly Sales | ACOS |\n|--------|------------------|------------------|------|\n| March (Weeks 5-8) | $6,716 | $41,928 | 16.0% |\n| April-May (Weeks 9-13) | $11,500 | $58,769 | 19.9% |\n\n- Spend increased 71% ($6.7K → $11.5K)\n- Sales increased only 40% ($41.9K → $58.8K)\n- **Result**: ACOS increased 24% (16.0% → 19.9%)\n\n**2. Diminishing Returns from Scaling**\n- Week 10: Spend doubled to $14K, but ACOS jumped to 19.4%\n- Aggressive scaling hit less efficient keywords/placements\n- Law of diminishing returns in effect\n\n**3. Possible Campaign Changes**\n- New campaigns launched in early April?\n- Bid increases implemented?\n- Targeting expansion to lower-quality keywords?\n\n**4. Seasonal Factors**\n- Post-Q1 slowdown in April?\n- Increased competition in April-May?\n- Category-specific seasonality?\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### Immediate Actions (Week 14+)\n\n**1. Reduce Spend to March Levels**\n- Target: $7-8K/week (down from current $11-12K)\n- Focus on high-ROAS campaigns only\n- Pause or reduce budget on campaigns with ACOS >25%\n\n**2. Return to Week 8 Strategy**\n- Week 8 achieved 14.7% ACOS with $6.3K spend\n- Analyze what was different:\n  - Which campaigns were running?\n  - What were the bid levels?\n  - Which keywords were active?\n- Replicate that winning formula\n\n**3. Audit April Changes**\n- Review all campaign changes made in early April\n- Identify what triggered the ACOS increase\n- Reverse unsuccessful changes\n\n**4. Tighten Targeting**\n- Add negative keywords from April-May period\n- Pause low-performing keywords (ACOS >30%)\n- Focus budget on proven converters from March\n\n### Strategic Recommendations\n\n**1. Set ACOS Targets by Phase**\n- **Target ACOS**: 16-17% (March levels)\n- **Maximum ACOS**: 19% (current is 21.1%)\n- **Optimal spend**: $7-9K/week\n\n**2. Controlled Scaling Approach**\n- Don't increase spend >20% week-over-week\n- Monitor ACOS daily during scaling\n- Pull back immediately if ACOS exceeds 18%\n\n**3. Campaign Segmentation**\n- **Tier 1** (ACOS <15%): Scale aggressively\n- **Tier 2** (ACOS 15-20%): Maintain current spend\n- **Tier 3** (ACOS >20%): Reduce spend by 50%\n\n**4. Weekly Monitoring**\n- Track ACOS every Monday\n- Alert if ACOS >18% for 3 consecutive days\n- Monthly review of 4-week rolling average\n\n## Expected Impact\n\n**If recommendations implemented:**\n\n**Week 14-17 Targets:**\n- Weekly spend: $7-8K (down from $11-12K)\n- Target ACOS: 16-17% (down from 21.1%)\n- Expected sales: $45-50K/week\n- ROAS: 5.5-6.0 (up from 4.74)\n\n**Monthly Impact:**\n- Save $12-16K/month in wasted ad spend\n- Improve ACOS by 4-5 percentage points\n- Maintain or slightly reduce sales (acceptable tradeoff)\n- Improve profitability significantly\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**Verdict**: **TREND, not noise**\n\nThe data shows a clear upward trend in ACOS from March's optimal 16.0% to May's problematic 21.1%. This is driven by aggressive spend increases in April that hit diminishing returns. \n\n**Action Required**: Reduce spend to March levels ($7-8K/week) and replicate the Week 8 strategy that achieved 14.7% ACOS.\n\n**Timeline**: Expect 2-3 weeks to return to 16-17% ACOS after implementing changes.\n"
