          "label": "Sonnet 4.5",
          "content": "# EV167: ACOS Change Decomposition Analysis\n\n## Overall ACOS Change\n\n| Period | Spend | Sales | ACOS | ROAS |\n|--------|-------|-------|------|------|\n| **Prior 30 Days** (Mar 9 - Apr 7) | $28,623 | $180,547 | **15.9%** | 6.31 |\n| **Current 30 Days** (Apr 8 - May 7) | $52,410 | $261,105 | **20.1%** | 4.98 |\n| **Change** | +$23,787 (+83%) | +$80,558 (+45%) | **+4.2 pp** | -1.33 |\n\n**ACOS increased from 15.9% to 20.1% (+4.2 percentage points, +26% relative increase)**\n\n## Decomposition Analysis\n\n### 1. Spend Effect\n**Spend increased 83%** ($28.6K → $52.4K)\n- Additional spend: +$23,787\n- If efficiency remained constant (15.9% ACOS), this would generate: $149,604 in sales\n- **Actual sales from increased spend**: $80,558\n- **Efficiency**: Only 54% of expected sales achieved\n\n**Conclusion**: Aggressive spend increase hit diminishing returns\n\n### 2. Sales Efficiency Effect\n**Sales grew 45%** while spend grew 83%\n- Spend growth outpaced sales growth by 38 percentage points\n- **Marginal ACOS** on incremental spend: 29.5%\n  - Calculation: $23,787 / $80,558 = 29.5%\n- This is 13.6 pp worse than baseline 15.9% ACOS\n\n**Conclusion**: New spend was significantly less efficient\n\n### 3. Compositional Shifts\n\n**Top 5 Positive Contributors (Increased ACOS):**\n\n| ASIN | ACOS Impact | Current ACOS | Prior ACOS | Spend Change |\n|------|-------------|--------------|------------|--------------|\n| B07XDBD4C4 | **+2.03 pp** | 28.9% | 23.7% | +$5,646 (+730%) |\n| B006NONHNE | +1.64 pp | 10.7% | 6.9% | +$4,627 (+586%) |\n| B09TQ2CW9L | +1.20 pp | 25.7% | 16.9% | +$3,161 (+4,377%) |\n| B081DK7DQH | +1.17 pp | 54.9% | 14.6% | +$3,056 (+10,726%) |\n| B07XKW55KJ | +0.73 pp | 15.3% | 14.4% | +$2,007 (+801%) |\n\n**Top 3 Negative Contributors (Decreased ACOS):**\n\n| ASIN | ACOS Impact | Current ACOS | Prior ACOS | Spend Change |\n|------|-------------|--------------|------------|--------------|\n| B01F209RSI | -0.35 pp | 85.2% | 86.1% | -$256 (-17%) |\n| B003O6MY6U | -0.32 pp | 76.5% | 84.0% | -$314 (-27%) |\n| B07C9H3ZX4 | -0.32 pp | 45.9% | 23.9% | -$497 (-67%) |\n\n## Single Biggest Contributor\n\n### **Winner: Diminishing Returns from Spend Scaling**\n\n**Evidence:**\n1. **Spend increased 83%** but sales only increased 45%\n2. **Marginal ACOS of 29.5%** on incremental $23.8K spend (vs. baseline 15.9%)\n3. **Top ASIN B07XDBD4C4** alone contributed +2.03 pp to ACOS increase\n   - Spend increased 730% ($773 → $6,420)\n   - ACOS worsened from 23.7% to 28.9%\n   - This single ASIN accounts for 48% of total ACOS increase\n\n**Root Cause**: Aggressive budget scaling in April pushed campaigns beyond their efficient spend threshold, particularly for B07XDBD4C4 which saw 7.3x spend increase with deteriorating efficiency.\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n### Why B07XDBD4C4 Drove ACOS Up\n\n**Performance Comparison:**\n| Metric | Prior | Current | Change |\n|--------|-------|---------|--------|\n| Spend | $773 | $6,420 | +730% |\n| Sales | $3,259 | $22,199 | +581% |\n| ACOS | 23.7% | 28.9% | +5.2 pp |\n| CVR | 13.6% | 11.8% | -1.8 pp |\n| CPC | $1.35 | $1.51 | +11.5% |\n\n**Issues:**\n- Spend grew faster than sales (730% vs. 581%)\n- CVR declined (13.6% → 11.8%)\n- CPC increased 11.5%\n- Hit less efficient keywords/placements at scale\n\n### Other Major Contributors\n\n**B081DK7DQH** (+1.17 pp impact):\n- Spend exploded 107x ($29 → $3,084)\n- ACOS skyrocketed from 14.6% to 54.9%\n- **Worst performer** - losing money at 54.9% ACOS\n- CVR collapsed from 6.7% to 1.7%\n\n**B09TQ2CW9L** (+1.20 pp impact):\n- Spend increased 44x ($72 → $3,233)\n- ACOS rose from 16.9% to 25.7%\n- Rapid scaling without optimization\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### Immediate Actions\n\n**1. Reduce Spend on Top ACOS Contributors**\n- **B081DK7DQH**: Cut spend by 80% (54.9% ACOS is unprofitable)\n- **B07XDBD4C4**: Reduce spend by 40% to March levels\n- **B09TQ2CW9L**: Reduce spend by 30%\n- **Target**: Save $5-7K/month, improve ACOS by 2-3 pp\n\n**2. Return to March Spend Levels**\n- March average: $6.7K/week (16.0% ACOS)\n- April-May average: $11.5K/week (19.9% ACOS)\n- **Target**: Reduce to $8-9K/week\n\n**3. Optimize High-Spend ASINs**\n- Review B07XDBD4C4 campaigns: Add negative keywords, reduce bids\n- Pause B081DK7DQH campaigns until listing/targeting is fixed\n- Tighten targeting on B09TQ2CW9L\n\n### Strategic Recommendations\n\n**1. Controlled Scaling Approach**\n- Don't increase ASIN spend >50% month-over-month\n- Monitor ACOS daily during scaling\n- Pull back if ACOS exceeds target by 3+ pp\n\n**2. ASIN-Level Targets**\n- **Tier 1** (ACOS <15%): Can scale aggressively\n- **Tier 2** (ACOS 15-20%): Scale cautiously\n- **Tier 3** (ACOS >25%): Reduce or pause\n\n**3. Efficiency Thresholds**\n- Set max ACOS: 20% account-wide\n- Alert if any ASIN exceeds 30% ACOS\n- Auto-reduce bids if ACOS >25% for 3 days\n\n## Expected Impact\n\n**After implementing recommendations:**\n\n**Month 1:**\n- Reduce spend from $52K to $35-40K (-25%)\n- Improve ACOS from 20.1% to 17-18% (-2-3 pp)\n- Sales may dip 10-15% (acceptable tradeoff)\n- Profitability improves significantly\n\n**Month 2-3:**\n- Stabilize at $40-45K spend\n- Target ACOS: 16-17%\n- Optimize top performers for controlled growth\n- Better ROI than current aggressive scaling\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**Single Biggest Contributor**: **Diminishing returns from 83% spend increase**\n\nThe ACOS increase from 15.9% to 20.1% is primarily driven by aggressive spend scaling that outpaced sales growth. The top ASIN B07XDBD4C4 alone accounts for 48% of the ACOS increase, with spend growing 730% while efficiency deteriorated.\n\n**Action Required**: Reduce spend by 25-30%, focus on efficient ASINs, and implement controlled scaling approach to return to 16-17% ACOS.\n"
