          "content": "# Why Has Overall Account Impression Volume Changed Over the Last 14 Days?\n\n## Data Window & File Summary\n\n| File | Rows | Date Range |\n|---|---|---|\n| `campaign_14d.json` | 138 | 2026-04-25 → 2026-05-08 (14-day totals per campaign) |\n| `campaign_week1.json` | 132 | 2026-04-25 → 2026-05-01 (daily rows, week 1) |\n| `keyword_14d.json` | 2,312 | 2026-04-25 → 2026-05-08 (keyword-level, cumulative ranges) |\n\n**Analysis period:** April 25 – May 8, 2026 (14 days)  \n**Week 1:** Apr 25 – May 1 | **Week 2:** May 2 – May 8\n\n---\n\n## Overall Impression Change\n\n| Period | Impressions | Spend |\n|---|---|---|\n| Week 1 (Apr 25–May 1) | 1,193,396 | $10,794.18 |\n| Week 2 (May 2–May 8) | 1,352,039 | $11,976.44 |\n| **WoW Change** | **+158,643 (+13.3%)** | **+$1,182.26 (+11.0%)** |\n\nImpressions grew **+13.3%** week-over-week. The analysis below tests four candidate causes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Bid Changes\n\n**Proxy metric:** Cost-per-click (CPC) change week-over-week (campaigns with ≥50 clicks each week).\n\n| Direction | # Campaigns | Notable Examples |\n|---|---|---|\n| CPC increase >10% (bids raised) | **4** | Hornady-Reloading_Case_Trimmer: +18.1%; Hornady-Auto_Charge_Pro (+13.8%); GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad phrases (+10–11%) |\n| CPC decrease >10% (bids cut) | **3** | GuardianSports-GC_Helmet_Cover: −19.0% (impressions +22,194); Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball: −14.1% (impressions +3,984); Arrow-CatchAll: −12.6% (impressions −1,749) |\n\n**Finding:** Bid changes are modest and net-mixed. The GuardianSports helmet cover campaign stands out — a 19% CPC reduction coincided with +22,194 impressions, consistent with a bid strategy shift toward volume. Hornady campaigns raised bids slightly but their impressions declined, suggesting bid increases alone did not drive the account-wide growth. **Bid changes explain a small portion of the increase.**\n\n---\n\n## 2. Budget Changes\n\n**Proxy metric:** Week-over-week spend growth vs. impression growth.\n\nTop campaigns by spend increase (W1→W2):\n\n| Campaign | Imp Δ% | Spend Δ% | W2 Spend |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids-MULTI-NB-SP-EXACT | +1,380% | +1,798% | $60.34 |\n| Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids_Blue-NB-SP-EXACT | +1,419% | +681% | $66.01 |\n| Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids-Branded-Exact | +541% | +514% | $105.40 |\n| Petkin-Paw_Wipes_Orange-NB-SP-Exact | +307% | +162% | $160.16 |\n| GPS-Cool_Pet_Pad_Medium-NB-SP-Exact | NEW | NEW | — |\n\n**Finding:** Several campaigns had near-zero spend in W1 and ramped sharply in W2, driving large impression increases. Frogglez swim goggles campaigns (collectively +54,868 impressions) and Petkin-Paw Wipes (+16,976 impressions) saw spend roughly match or exceed impression growth, indicating **budget was increased or newly allocated**. Six campaigns were entirely absent from week 1 and activated in week 2, contributing **39,606 net-new impressions**. **Budget expansion is the primary driver of the WoW growth.**\n\n---\n\n## 3. Search Volume Changes (Proxy: Impressions per Keyword)\n\nTop keywords by 14-day impression volume:\n\n| Keyword | 14d Impressions |\n|---|---|\n| loose-match (auto) | 136,850 |\n| hornady | 124,658 |\n| cooling mat dogs | 121,747 |\n| helmet | 102,993 |\n| cooling mats for dogs | 90,519 |\n| cooling mat for dogs | 85,200 |\n| dog cooling mat | 83,670 |\n\n**Finding:** Keyword-level data uses cumulative date ranges rather than daily breakdowns, so direct W1/W2 keyword comparison is limited to the 10 keywords with week-1 range records (all low-volume flagpole/headgear terms). However, the category-level pattern is clear: **pet cooling pad keywords** (cooling mat dogs, dog cooling mat, cooling mats for dogs, cooling pad for dog, etc.) dominate the top keyword impression volume — consistent with seasonal summer demand lifting impression availability in W2. This aligns with campaign-level increases for GPS-GPetShop Cool Pet Pad (+8,178 impressions) and GPS-Chillz Pet Pad (+9,310 impressions). **Rising search volume for seasonal summer pet products partially explains the W2 impression uplift.**\n\n---\n\n## 4. Campaign Status Changes\n\n| Status Change | Count | Impression Impact |\n|---|---|---|\n| Campaigns newly active in W2 (absent from W1) | **6** | +39,606 impressions |\n| Campaigns paused in W2 (absent from W2) | **0** | — |\n\nNew/reactivated campaigns in W2:\n- `GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad_Medium-NB-SP-Exact`: 27,065 impressions\n- `Petkin-Dog_Sunscreen-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact`: 7,305 impressions\n- `GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad_Medium-NB-SP-Phrase`: 5,003 impressions\n- Others: ~200 impressions combined\n\n**Finding:** No campaigns were turned off in W2, but 6 campaigns launched/reactivated, adding ~39,606 impressions (roughly 25% of the total WoW gain). **Campaign activation changes partially explain the increase.**\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Factor | Direction | Magnitude | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Bid changes | Mixed | Small (4 raised, 3 cut) | Minor factor |\n| Budget expansion / new campaigns | Increase | ~39,606 from new + high growth from ramped spend | **Primary driver** |\n| Search volume (seasonal demand) | Increase | Pet cooling pads dominate top keywords; seasonal uplift evident | **Contributing factor** |\n| Campaign status changes | Net positive (6 new, 0 paused) | +39,606 impressions | **Secondary driver** |\n\n**Root cause:** The +158,643 (+13.3%) impression increase in week 2 is primarily driven by **budget expansion** — several campaigns (especially Frogglez swim goggles and Petkin pet wipes) ramped from near-zero to significant spend, and 6 campaigns activated for the first time. A seasonal tailwind in **summer pet cooling product search volume** amplified available impression inventory. Bid changes were minor and mixed, with no single campaign showing a bid-driven impression breakout.\n"
