          "label": "Sonnet 4.6",
          "content": "# NTB Share Change Analysis\n\n**Data window:** Prior 30 days: 2026-03-09 – 2026-04-07 | Last 30 days: 2026-04-08 – 2026-05-07  \n**Report rows:** 150 (prior period) + 148 (last period) = 298 total  \n**Account:** Firefly Buys (`amzn1.ads-account.g.bj313q92siafngzbl54ewi56r`)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nNTB purchase share rose **+1.79 percentage points**, from **3.25% → 5.05%**. The shift is primarily driven by **higher Sponsored Brands (SB) volume**, which accounts for ~77% of the move. The remaining ~23% comes from an improvement in the SB NTB conversion rate. SP composition also shifted materially, but that change had no direct NTB impact (SP reports zero NTB in this account).\n\n---\n\n## NTB Share Movement\n\n| Metric | Prior 30 (Mar 9 – Apr 7) | Last 30 (Apr 8 – May 7) | Change |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Total purchases | 5,199 | 5,728 | +529 (+10%) |\n| NTB purchases | 169 | 289 | +120 (+71%) |\n| **NTB share** | **3.25%** | **5.05%** | **+1.79 pp** |\n| Total sales | $192,489 | $275,237 | +43% |\n| NTB sales | $8,848 | $15,718 | +78% |\n| Total ad spend | $30,073 | $54,354 | +81% |\n\n---\n\n## Driver Decomposition\n\nSince 100% of NTB purchases come from Sponsored Brands (SP records zero NTB in this account), the NTB share equation simplifies to:\n\n> **NTB share = SB purchase share × SB NTB rate**\n\nA Shapley-style decomposition of the +1.79 pp change:\n\n| Driver | Contribution |\n|---|---|\n| SB volume (purchase share: 4.73% → 6.63%) | **+1.38 pp** (77%) |\n| SB NTB rate (68.7% → 76.1%) | **+0.42 pp** (23%) |\n| **Total** | **+1.79 pp** |\n\n**Primary driver: growth in SB volume.** SB purchases rose 55% (246 → 380), while SP purchases rose only 8% (4,953 → 5,348). SB spend grew 46% ($1,450 → $2,122) and SB impressions grew 13% (416K → 470K).\n\n---\n\n## What Changed Within SB\n\nThe SB NTB rate improvement (+7.4 pp) was driven by campaign-level shifts:\n\n| Campaign | Prior NTB | Last NTB | Change |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pads-MULTI-NB-SB-Exact | 31 | 117 | +86 |\n| GPS-GPetShop_Disney_Lilo&Stitch-Branded-SB-Phrase | 41 | 62 | +21 |\n| WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT | 31 | 41 | +10 |\n| Guardian Sports-GC_Helmet_Cover_For_Football-Branded-SB-Phrase | 28 | 22 | −6 |\n\nThe NB SB campaign for GPetShop Pet Pads alone accounts for 86 of the 120 net new NTB purchases — nearly three-quarters of the total NTB gain.\n\n---\n\n## SP Composition Shift\n\nSP composition changed dramatically but did not affect NTB share directly (SP drives 0 NTB). The shift is still worth noting as context:\n\n| Brand | Prior SP purchases | Last SP purchases | Change |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| GPS (GPetShop pet pads) | 959 (19.4%) | 2,224 (41.6%) | +132% |\n| Petkin | 1,314 (26.5%) | 693 (13.0%) | −47% |\n| Arrow | 566 (11.4%) | 286 (5.3%) | −49% |\n| WineRX | 482 (9.7%) | 380 (7.1%) | −21% |\n\nGPS/GPetShop pet-pad products surged to dominate SP, concurrent with the SB campaign ramp for the same brand. This suggests a coordinated push on GPS products — both via SP (driving volume and repeat) and SB NB campaigns (capturing new-to-brand shoppers).\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe +1.79 pp NTB share increase is driven by **a higher SB spend share, not a fundamental change in SP composition or overall product mix** (those only affect NTB indirectly). Specifically:\n\n1. **SB volume grew disproportionately** (+55% purchases vs. +8% SP) → accounts for 77% of the NTB share gain.\n2. **SB NTB rate improved** (+7.4 pp), mainly from the GPS Pet Pads NB SB Exact campaign, which tripled its NTB output → accounts for the remaining 23%.\n3. **SP product mix shifted heavily toward GPS/GPetShop**, which mirrors the SB ramp — indicating a full-funnel expansion of GPS products rather than an organic category shift.\n"
