          "label": "Sonnet 4.5",
          "content": "# EV171: NTB Share Change Analysis\n\n## NTB Share Change\n\n| Period | NTB Orders | Total Orders | NTB Share | NTB Sales |\n|--------|------------|--------------|-----------|-----------|\n| **Prior 30 Days** | 169 | 5,199 | **3.25%** | $8,848 |\n| **Current 30 Days** | 294 | 5,838 | **5.04%** | $15,891 |\n| **Change** | +125 (+74%) | +639 (+12%) | **+1.79 pp** | +$7,043 (+80%) |\n\n**NTB share increased from 3.25% to 5.04% (+1.79 percentage points, +55% relative increase)**\n\n## Root Cause: SB Volume Increase\n\n### NTB by Ad Type\n\n**Current Period:**\n| Ad Type | Orders | NTB Orders | NTB Share | Spend | NTB Sales |\n|---------|--------|------------|-----------|-------|-----------|\n| **SP** | 5,453 | 0 | **0%** | $52,487 | $0 |\n| **SB** | 385 | 294 | **76.4%** | $2,150 | $15,891 |\n| **Total** | 5,838 | 294 | 5.04% | $54,637 | $15,891 |\n\n**Prior Period:**\n| Ad Type | Orders | NTB Orders | NTB Share | Spend | NTB Sales |\n|---------|--------|------------|-----------|-------|-----------|\n| **SP** | 4,953 | 0 | **0%** | $28,623 | $0 |\n| **SB** | 246 | 169 | **68.7%** | $1,450 | $8,848 |\n| **Total** | 5,199 | 169 | 3.25% | $30,073 | $8,848 |\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**1. SB Drives 100% of NTB**\n- SP contributes 0 NTB orders (both periods)\n- SB contributes all 294 NTB orders in current period\n- **SB is the sole NTB driver**\n\n**2. SB Volume Increased Significantly**\n- SB spend: +48% ($1,450 → $2,150)\n- SB orders: +57% (246 → 385)\n- SB NTB orders: +74% (169 → 294)\n- **SB scaling directly drove NTB increase**\n\n**3. SB NTB Share Also Improved**\n- Prior: 68.7% of SB orders were NTB\n- Current: 76.4% of SB orders were NTB\n- **+7.7 pp improvement** in SB NTB efficiency\n\n## Decomposition Analysis\n\n### Contribution to 1.79 pp NTB Share Increase\n\n**Factor 1: SB Volume Increase** (+1.24 pp)\n- SB orders increased from 246 to 385 (+139 orders)\n- At prior NTB rate (68.7%), this would add: 95 NTB orders\n- Impact on overall NTB share: +1.24 pp\n- **Contribution: 69% of total increase**\n\n**Factor 2: SB NTB Efficiency Improvement** (+0.55 pp)\n- SB NTB share improved from 68.7% to 76.4% (+7.7 pp)\n- On 385 SB orders, this adds: 30 NTB orders\n- Impact on overall NTB share: +0.55 pp\n- **Contribution: 31% of total increase**\n\n**Factor 3: SP Composition Change** (0 pp)\n- SP still has 0% NTB\n- No change in SP NTB contribution\n- **Contribution: 0%**\n\n**Factor 4: Product Mix Change** (Minimal)\n- Overall order mix shifted slightly toward SB (4.7% → 6.6% of orders)\n- This is captured in Factor 1 (SB volume increase)\n- **Contribution: Included in Factor 1**\n\n## Single Biggest Driver\n\n**Winner: SB Volume Increase (69% contribution)**\n\n**Evidence:**\n- SB spend increased 48% ($1,450 → $2,150)\n- SB orders increased 57% (246 → 385)\n- This volume increase alone accounts for 1.24 pp of the 1.79 pp NTB share increase\n- **SB scaling is the primary driver**\n\n**Secondary Factor:** SB NTB efficiency improved from 68.7% to 76.4%, contributing additional 0.55 pp\n\n## Why SB Drives NTB (and SP Doesn't)\n\n### Sponsored Brands Characteristics\n- **Top-of-funnel**: Captures customers early in discovery\n- **Brand awareness**: Introduces brand to new customers\n- **Broad reach**: Category-level keywords attract new audiences\n- **Visual branding**: Logo and brand name prominent\n- **Multiple products**: Showcases product range\n\n### Sponsored Products Characteristics\n- **Bottom-of-funnel**: Captures customers ready to buy\n- **Product-specific**: Targets existing demand\n- **Repeat customers**: Often attracts customers who know what they want\n- **No NTB tracking**: SP reports don't include NTB metrics (shows 0%)\n\n**Note**: SP showing 0% NTB may be a data limitation rather than actual performance. SP likely drives some NTB, but it's not tracked in current reports.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### Immediate Actions\n\n**1. Continue Scaling SB**\n- Current SB spend: $2,150/month (4% of total)\n- Target: $3,000-4,000/month (7-8% of total)\n- **Rationale**: SB is highly efficient at driving NTB (76.4% NTB rate)\n\n**2. Optimize SB for NTB**\n- Focus on category keywords (not branded)\n- Use video ads for engagement\n- Target competitor keywords\n- Expand to new product categories\n\n**3. Increase SB Budget Allocation**\n- Current mix: 96% SP, 4% SB\n- Target mix: 85% SP, 15% SB\n- **Expected impact**: NTB share could reach 8-10%\n\n### Strategic Recommendations\n\n**1. Set NTB Targets**\n- Current: 5.04% NTB share\n- 3-month target: 7-8% NTB share\n- 6-month target: 10% NTB share\n- **Strategy**: Scale SB to $5K/month\n\n**2. Launch SD for NTB**\n- SD (Sponsored Display) also drives NTB\n- Use remarketing to capture new visitors\n- Target competitor product pages\n- **Expected**: 20-30% NTB rate from SD\n\n**3. Test SB Video Ads**\n- Video ads have higher engagement\n- Better for brand storytelling\n- Typically higher NTB rates\n- **Pilot**: $500/month video budget\n\n**4. Expand SB Keyword Coverage**\n- Current: 37 SB campaigns\n- Add 20-30 new category keywords\n- Focus on high-volume, low-competition terms\n- **Expected**: +50 NTB orders/month\n\n## Expected Impact\n\n**After implementing recommendations (3 months):**\n\n**SB Scaling:**\n- SB spend: $2,150 → $4,000 (+86%)\n- SB orders: 385 → 715 (+86%)\n- SB NTB orders: 294 → 546 (+86%)\n\n**Overall NTB Impact:**\n- Total NTB orders: 294 → 546 (+86%)\n- Total orders: 5,838 → 6,500 (+11%)\n- **NTB share: 5.04% → 8.4%** (+3.4 pp)\n\n**Business Impact:**\n- New customer acquisition: +252 customers/month\n- Long-term value: Higher LTV from new customers\n- Brand growth: Reduced reliance on repeat customers\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**Primary Driver**: **SB volume increase** (69% contribution)\n\nThe NTB share increase from 3.25% to 5.04% is primarily driven by a 48% increase in SB spend, which generated 125 additional NTB orders. SB is the sole NTB driver in the account (SP shows 0% NTB), making SB scaling the most effective strategy for new customer acquisition.\n\n**Action Required**: Continue scaling SB investment from current 4% to target 15% of total ad spend to reach 8-10% NTB share within 6 months.\n"
