          "content": "Based on the provided data, the change in New-To-Brand (NTB) share over the last 30 days is actually being driven by a combination of **all three factors**: a massive shift in SP composition diluting overall share, offset by a significant increase in SB volume, which was fueled by a highly specific change in the product mix. \n\nHere is the breakdown of exactly what is driving the changes:\n\n### 1. Change in Product Mix & SB Volume (The NTB Growth Drivers)\nSponsored Brands (SB) are the only ad products reporting NTB metrics in your dataset. Within the SB portfolio, both volume and NTB efficiency skyrocketed, driven almost entirely by one specific product line: **GPS Pet Pads**.\n\n*   **SB Volume Doubled:** Total SB sales grew from **~$9,831** in the prior 30 days to **~$18,111** in the last 30 days. \n*   **SB NTB Share Increased:** The NTB share *within* your Sponsored Brands campaigns actually improved significantly, jumping from **75.9%** ($7,465 NTB Sales) in the prior 30 days to **83.6%** ($15,144 NTB Sales) in the last 30 days.\n*   **The Product Mix Driver:** The absolute biggest driver of this NTB growth is the `GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pads-MULTI-NB-SB-Exact` campaign. \n    *   *Prior 30:* $1,901 in NTB Sales\n    *   *Last 30:* **$7,713 in NTB Sales** (out of $8,578 total sales)\n    *   The `GPS-GPetShop_Disney_Lilo&Stitch-Branded-SB-Phrase` campaign also saw strong NTB growth, jumping from $2,383 to $3,929 in NTB Sales. \n\n### 2. Change in SP Composition (The Dilution Effect)\nWhile your SB campaigns generated record NTB sales, your **overall account NTB share** (if calculated across total sales) is being heavily diluted by a massive explosion in Sponsored Products (SP) volume. \n\nBecause SP campaigns do not report NTB metrics in this dataset (they register as `null`), any increase in SP sales shrinks the overall reported NTB percentage. In the last 30 days, SP sales grew at an even faster rate than SB sales, again driven by the GPS Pet Pads:\n*   `GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact` exploded from **$6,371** to **$36,489** in sales.\n*   `GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase` grew from **$11,082** to **$31,553** in sales.\n*   `GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase` surged from **$2,264** to **$22,539** in sales.\n\n### Summary Conclusion\nIf you are looking at a **drop in overall NTB share**, it is entirely driven by the **SP composition change**—specifically, the explosive growth of SP Pet Pad campaigns diluting the metric. \n\nHowever, if you are looking at the **growth in absolute NTB volume or SB NTB share**, it is being driven by a **change in product mix and SB volume**—specifically, the aggressive scaling of the exact-match SB campaign for GPS Pet Pads, which is converting new-to-brand customers at an incredibly high >89% rate."
