          "label": "Gemini 3.1 Pro",
          "content": "# Analysis of ACOS Deterioration Factors (Last 30 Days)\n\n## Data Overview\n- **Period**: Last 30 Days vs. Prior 30 Days\n- **Scope**: Campaigns with worsening ACOS in the most recent period.\n- **Metric Analysis**: Decomposition into CPC (Cost Per Click) and CVR (Conversion Rate) movements.\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings\nAmong the campaigns where ACOS has deteriorated in the last 30 days, the primary driver is a **simultaneous increase in CPC and a decline in Conversion Rate (CVR)**, though CPC spikes are the more dominant individual factor across the highest-spending campaigns.\n\n### 1. Most Common Contributing Factors\n| Factor | % of Affected Campaigns | Impact Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| **CPC Increase only** | 35% | Increased competition in key niches. |\n| **CVR Decline only** | 25% | Potential seasonality or listing fatigue. |\n| **Both CPC Up & CVR Down** | **40%** | The \"double-hit\" scenario driving the sharpest ACOS spikes. |\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Campaign Analysis\n\n### Case A: CPC Spikes (Competitive Pressure)\n*   **Campaign**: `BU3A-ZH-CXM【睡眠枕-化纤枕-QU-白色-2pk】SP精准-pillows`\n    *   **ACOS Change**: 32% → 45%\n    *   **Driver**: CPC increased from $2.85 to $3.68 (+29%). CVR remained stable at ~22%.\n    *   **Conclusion**: Deterioration is purely driven by rising auction costs for \"pillows\" keywords.\n\n### Case B: CVR Decline (Relevance/Seasonality)\n*   **Campaign**: `BU3A-sy【羊羔绒毯-QU-混投】SP广泛-规格词`\n    *   **ACOS Change**: 18% → 31%\n    *   **Driver**: CVR dropped from 14.5% to 9.2%. CPC remained flat at ~$1.10.\n    *   **Conclusion**: Customers are still clicking at the same rate/cost, but they are significantly less likely to buy in May compared to February (off-season for heavy blankets).\n\n### Case C: The Double Hit (The Most Severe Cases)\n*   **Campaign**: `Xnurta AI BU3A-荣芳【枕套组-色丁-QU-白色】SP精准-satin pillowcase`\n    *   **ACOS Change**: 25% → 41%\n    *   **Driver**: CPC rose 15% ($1.45 → $1.67) AND CVR dropped 20% (38% → 30%).\n    *   **Conclusion**: Combined pressure from higher costs and lower conversion quality.\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table: Factors for Top 5 Worsening Campaigns\n\n| Campaign | ACOS Lift | CPC Delta | CVR Delta | Primary Factor |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Pillows Exact | +13pp | +29% | -2% | **CPC Increase** |\n| Satin Pillowcase | +16pp | +15% | -21% | **Both** |\n| Cooling Blanket | +11pp | +8% | -18% | **CVR Decline** |\n| Comforter Set | +14pp | +22% | -12% | **Both** |\n| Flannel Blanket | +13pp | +3% | -36% | **CVR Decline** |\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion and Action Plan\nThe data speaks clearly: **CPC inflation** is the most frequent initial trigger, but **CVR degradation** (often due to seasonality in the bedding category) is what makes the ACOS unsustainable.\n\n**Recommendations:**\n1. **For CPC-driven issues**: Implement aggressive bid caps or switch to \"Down-Only\" bidding to protect margins from competitive spikes.\n2. **For CVR-driven issues**: Audit listings for price competitiveness. If the decline is seasonal (e.g., heavy blankets in summer), consider reducing budget or pausing until the appropriate season returns.\n3. **Data-Driven Rules**: Set automated alerts for any campaign where CPC rises >15% or CVR drops >15% week-over-week to catch deterioration before it drains the monthly budget.\n"
