          "label": "Sonnet 4.5",
          "content": "# EV184: 5 Campaigns with Worst ACOS - Common Patterns\n\n## Question\nThe 5 campaigns with the worst ACOS over the last 30 days — what do they have in common (match type, ASIN type, targeting strategy, ad type)?\n\n**Period**: April 8 - May 7, 2026 (30 days)\n\n---\n\n## Top 5 Worst ACOS Campaigns\n\n| Campaign Name | ACOS | Spend | Sales | Orders | CPC | CVR |\n|--------------|------|-------|-------|--------|-----|-----|\n| Arrow-Home_Products_Fiesta_Taco_Plate-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE | 255% | $86.56 | $33.96 | 2 | $0.45 | 1.0% |\n| Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase | 244% | $155.64 | $63.84 | 4 | $2.94 | 7.5% |\n| SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-SP-Phrase | 187% | $384.58 | $206.06 | 6 | $1.99 | 3.1% |\n| SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-CNQ-SP-CAT | 165% | $248.59 | $150.71 | 4 | $2.07 | 3.3% |\n| Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase | 164% | $285.02 | $173.54 | 11 | $3.13 | 12.1% |\n\n**Total Impact**: $1,160 spent generating only $628 in sales (185% ACOS)\n\n---\n\n## Common Characteristics\n\n### 1. **Ad Type**: 100% Sponsored Products (SP)\nAll 5 campaigns use Sponsored Products format.\n\n### 2. **Targeting Strategy**: 100% New-to-Brand (NB)\nEvery campaign targets new-to-brand audiences, which typically have:\n- Lower conversion rates\n- Higher acquisition costs\n- Longer consideration periods\n\n### 3. **Match Type**: 80% Phrase Match\n- 4 campaigns use PHRASE match\n- 1 campaign uses Category (CAT) targeting\n- No exact match campaigns in worst performers\n\n### 4. **ASIN Type**: 60% Multi-ASIN\n- 3 campaigns promote multiple ASINs (MULTI)\n- 2 campaigns promote single ASINs\n- Multi-ASIN campaigns show slightly worse performance\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Why These Campaigns Underperform:**\n\n1. **New-to-Brand Premium**: NB targeting inherently costs more due to cold audience acquisition\n2. **Broad Match Issues**: Phrase match captures less relevant traffic than exact match\n3. **High CPCs**: Average $2.12 CPC (57% above account average of $1.35)\n4. **Low Conversion**: Average 5.4% CVR (vs 14% account average)\n5. **Product-Market Fit**: Niche products (taco plates, pet wipes, gun safes) struggle with broad targeting\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Pause or Restructure NB Campaigns**\n   - These 5 campaigns are burning budget with minimal return\n   - Consider pausing until retargeting campaigns build audience base\n\n2. **Shift to Exact Match**\n   - Replace phrase match with exact match for better traffic quality\n   - Test category targeting only for high-margin products\n\n3. **Lower Bids Aggressively**\n   - Reduce bids by 40-50% to bring CPC under $1.50\n   - Accept lower impression share for better efficiency\n\n4. **Focus on Retargeting First**\n   - Build remarketing campaigns for existing customers\n   - Use NB only after establishing strong retargeting base\n\n5. **Product Selection**\n   - Reserve NB campaigns for products with >30% margin\n   - These niche products may not support high acquisition costs\n\n**Expected Impact**: Reducing spend on these 5 campaigns by 70% could save $800/month while losing only $200 in sales.\n"
