          "label": "Opus 4.7",
          "content": "# The 5 Worst-ACOS Campaigns — What Do They Have in Common?\n\n## Data window & scope\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**.\n- Report: keyword-level, 2,603 rows aggregated to campaign; 130 campaigns with ≥ 20 clicks (the meaningful-volume set).\n- Five \"zero-sales\" campaigns were excluded from the worst list (they'd technically be infinite ACOS, but with so few clicks they aren't informative).\n\n## 5 worst-ACOS campaigns (meaningful volume, sales > 0)\n\n| Rank | Campaign (trunc.) | ACOS | Spend | Clicks | Match type | Ad type | ASIN type |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes MULTI NB SP Phrase | **244%** | $156 | 53 | PHRASE | SP | MULTI (multi-SKU) |\n| 2 | Arrow-Home_Products_Fiesta_Taco_Plate MULTI NB SP PHRASE | **236%** | $80 | 182 | PHRASE | SP | MULTI |\n| 3 | SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box B06XQVYY24 NB SP Phrase | **183%** | $310 | 158 | PHRASE | SP | Single ASIN |\n| 4 | SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box B06XQVYY24 NB CNQ SP CAT | **165%** | $249 | 120 | (category) | SP | Single ASIN |\n| 5 | Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes MULTI NB SP Phrase | **164%** | $285 | 91 | PHRASE | SP | MULTI |\n\n## What do they have in common?\n\n### 1. Match type\n- **4 of 5 are PHRASE match** (the fifth is a category/auto variant on SnapSafe Treklite). **None are EXACT.**\n- Within the top 20 worst-ACOS campaigns (spot-checked): PHRASE dominates.\n- **Conclusion**: PHRASE match is the worst-ACOS match type on this account, at least in this sample.\n\n### 2. ASIN type\n- **3 of 5 are MULTI-SKU campaigns** (`Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes MULTI`, `Arrow-...MULTI`, `Petkin-MegaValuPak MULTI`). MULTI means the campaign targets multiple child ASINs.\n- 2 are single-ASIN SnapSafe Treklite (B06XQVYY24).\n- **Conclusion**: MULTI-SKU campaigns are over-represented — the wider ASIN set + broad match makes relevance harder.\n\n### 3. Targeting strategy\n- 4 of 5 are **non-branded (NB)** campaigns — targeting generic queries rather than brand terms.\n- 1 is category targeting (`SnapSafe-...CNQ SP CAT`).\n- **Conclusion**: NB + wide match = auction-price pressure without enough intent to convert.\n\n### 4. Ad type\n- **All 5 are Sponsored Products (SP)**. None are SB or SBV.\n- **Conclusion**: on this account, the worst-ACOS failures all sit in SP. SB/SBV failures exist but at smaller dollar scale (see EV088 / EV064).\n\n### 5. Product category\n- 3 of 5 are **Petkin pet wipes** — this product category is a known problem on this profile (consistent with EV057 and EV064).\n- 2 of 5 are **SnapSafe Treklite Gun Safe** — another consistent problem category.\n- Arrow Home Products Fiesta Taco Plate (Plate AOV is low; broad match on generic \"taco plate\" queries blows ACOS).\n- **Conclusion**: **low-AOV products run on broad match in head-term queries** is the dominant pattern. The product can't carry the CPC at the match type's natural query quality.\n\n## Common thread\nEvery one of these 5 campaigns runs **wide match (PHRASE or Category) on generic (non-brand) queries** for a **low-to-mid AOV product**. The economics don't work: CPC > product-margin-per-sale × CVR.\n\n## Recommendations\n1. **Switch PHRASE → EXACT for these 5 campaigns**. Lose some discovery breadth, but ACOS drops meaningfully.\n2. **Pause the 5 \"zero-sales\" campaigns** (not in the table but found in the same cohort) — DelkProducts and Hornady/SnapSafe small-volume items converting zero.\n3. **For MULTI-SKU campaigns, split into single-SKU** — campaigns targeting multiple child ASINs confuse Amazon's relevance scoring.\n4. **Review Petkin pet-wipes portfolio** account-wide. Consistent high-ACOS pattern across pet-wipes campaigns means the product line needs a price/margin review, not just bid adjustments.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **ASIN-level margin and AOV** — needed to confirm the \"low AOV product can't support head-term PHRASE\" hypothesis.\n- **Previous-period performance** — to distinguish chronic from recent degradation.\n- **Search-term detail** for each of the 5 campaigns — to confirm whether it's specific queries or broad degradation.\n- **Competitor CPC** in the pet-wipes and gun-safe categories — to understand whether these campaigns were ever viable or have always been structurally wrong.\n"
