          "label": "Gemini 3.1 Pro",
          "content": "Based on the provided data summary, I have aggregated the total cost and total sales for each campaign to calculate their ACOS (Advertising Cost of Sales = Total Cost / Total Sales). \n\nEvaluating the campaigns that generated sales, here are the **5 campaigns with the worst (highest) ACOS** over the last 30 days:\n\n1. **Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact**\n   * Spend: $94.04 | Sales: $14.99 | **ACOS: 627.3%**\n2. **Petkin-Pet_Dental_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase**\n   * Spend: $28.98 | Sales: $11.93 | **ACOS: 242.9%**\n3. **Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase**\n   * Spend: $30.81 | Sales: $14.99 | **ACOS: 205.5%**\n4. **Hornady-Auto_Charge_Pro_Powder_Measure-B081DJPYM8-NB-SP-PHRASE**\n   * Spend: $57.16 | Sales: $46.84 | **ACOS: 122.0%**\n5. **Petkin-Paw_Wipes_Orange-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact**\n   * Spend: $150.78 | Sales: $152.36 | **ACOS: 98.9%**\n\n### What They Have in Common\n\nBy analyzing the naming conventions of these 5 campaigns, we can break down their attributes:\n\n*   **Targeting Strategy:** **All 5 campaigns share the \"NB\" (Non-Branded) targeting strategy.**\n*   **Ad Type:** **All 5 campaigns share the \"SP\" (Sponsored Products) ad type.**\n*   **Match Type:** They do *not* share a match type (they are a mix of Exact and Phrase matches).\n*   **ASIN Type:** They do *not* share an ASIN type (4 are \"MULTI\" ASIN campaigns, while 1 targets a single ASIN \"B081DJPYM8\").\n\n**Conclusion:** \nThe common thread among your worst-performing campaigns by ACOS is that they are all **Non-Branded Sponsored Products** campaigns."
