          "content": "# 10 Search Terms to Promote to Manual Exact-Match Keywords\n\n**Data window:** 2026-04-09 to 2026-05-08 (30 days)  \n**Account:** Firefly Buys (`amzn1.ads-account.g.bj313q92siafngzbl54ewi56r`)  \n**Total report rows:** 11,853  \n**Unique (search term × campaign) combinations:** 11,853  \n\n---\n\n## Methodology\n\nSearch terms were aggregated across the 30-day window and filtered to candidates that:\n\n1. Appeared in a **non-exact-match** campaign (phrase, broad, auto, or ASIN-targeting).\n2. Are **not already covered** by an existing exact-match campaign in this account (1,080 terms excluded).\n3. Had **≥ 5 clicks** over the period.\n\nCandidates were ranked by **purchases** (descending), then **sales**, then **clicks**. The recommended starting bid is set at **CPC × 1.10** — a modest premium to secure impression share in a new exact keyword without overpaying.\n\n---\n\n## Top 10 Recommendations\n\n| # | Search Term | Target Campaign (add exact keyword here) | Clicks | Purchases | Sales (USD) | ROAS | Current CPC | Rec. Starting Bid |\n|---|-------------|------------------------------------------|-------:|----------:|------------:|-----:|------------:|------------------:|\n| 1 | `green pet cooling mat` | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 483 | 135 | $8,200.57 | 13.45 | $1.26 | **$1.39** |\n| 2 | `the green pet shop cool pet pad` | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 354 | 106 | $5,778.36 | 13.07 | $1.25 | **$1.38** |\n| 3 | `green pet shop cool pet pad` | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 238 | 73 | $4,606.72 | 19.20 | $1.01 | **$1.11** |\n| 4 | `B07P6SNV19` ¹ | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN | 66 | 31 | $598.14 | 23.47 | $0.39 | **$0.43** |\n| 5 | `big and thick pet wipes for dogs` | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 96 | 29 | $572.56 | 3.01 | $1.98 | **$2.18** |\n| 6 | `green pet shop cooling mat` | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 108 | 28 | $1,659.72 | 13.05 | $1.18 | **$1.30** |\n| 7 | `green pet shop cool pet pad` | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 88 | 24 | $1,194.76 | 13.97 | $0.97 | **$1.07** |\n| 8 | `petkin pet wipes for dogs` | Petkin-Paw_Wipes_Orange-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 63 | 22 | $403.14 | 5.47 | $1.17 | **$1.29** |\n| 9 | `belly bones for medium dogs` | Fido-Treats_for_Dogs-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 32 | 20 | $688.43 | 11.90 | $1.81 | **$1.99** |\n| 10 | `the green pet shop cool pet pad` | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase | 66 | 19 | $1,065.79 | 16.88 | $0.96 | **$1.06** |\n\n¹ `B07P6SNV19` is an ASIN search query (customers searching the exact ASIN). For Sponsored Products you can add it as an exact keyword; alternatively consider adding it as a product (ASIN) target. Either way the economics ($0.39 CPC, 23× ROAS) strongly justify dedicated targeting.\n\n---\n\n## Reasoning\n\n- **Rows 1–3 and 6–7:** Branded variations of \"Green Pet Shop cool pet pad\" — these are high-intent, high-converting queries (ROAS 13–19×) currently captured only via phrase match. Locking them to exact match will reduce match dilution and prevent wasted spend on partial matches.\n- **Row 4:** ASIN-as-search-term with the highest ROAS in the set (23×) and low CPC ($0.39). Already in an ASIN-targeting campaign; adding an exact keyword or dedicated product target will reinforce coverage.\n- **Row 5:** \"big and thick pet wipes for dogs\" — lower ROAS (3×) but strong absolute purchase volume (29 conversions, $573 sales). CPC is higher ($1.98) so the starting bid ($2.18) should be reviewed after 2 weeks; if ROAS remains below target, adjust down.\n- **Row 8:** \"petkin pet wipes for dogs\" appears in a different Petkin campaign (Paw Wipes Orange) than the exact-match campaigns already covering it in the BigNThick campaign — confirming it is a genuine gap for this specific campaign.\n- **Row 9:** \"belly bones for medium dogs\" — niche, high-ROAS (11.9×) treats query with strong conversion rate (62.5% CVR on 32 clicks). Low click volume means the sample is moderate; monitor closely.\n- **Rows 7 and 10** use the same keyword phrase but target **different campaigns/products** (Chillz Pad vs. Cool Pet Pad), so both are valid separate recommendations.\n\n**Bid-setting logic:** Starting bid = current phrase-match CPC × 1.10 ensures the new exact keyword wins impressions immediately without overpaying. Revisit and adjust bids after 14 days of data once ACoS trends are visible.\n"
