          "content": "# 10 Search Terms to Promote to Manual Exact-Match — With Campaign and Starting Bid\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**.\n- Source: search-term performance. Candidates are terms that converted through phrase/broad/auto but have not yet been promoted to exact.\n\n## Top 10 promotion candidates\n\n| # | Search term | Observed CVR | Observed CPC | ROAS | Campaign to place it in | Recommended starting bid |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---|---:|\n| 1 | green pet cooling mat | 28.1% | $1.30 | 12.9 | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP (new EXACT group in same campaign) | **$1.50** (CPC × 1.15) |\n| 2 | the green pet shop cool pet pad | 30.1% | $1.21 | 13.7 | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP | **$1.40** |\n| 3 | green pet shop cool pet pad | 29.3% | $1.08 | 16.4 | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP | **$1.25** |\n| 4 | drop it wine drops | 46.2% | $0.85 | 10.2 | WineRX-Drop_It_Drops BRANDED SP (new EXACT group) | **$1.00** |\n| 5 | petkin pet wipes for dogs | 34.3% | $1.42 | 4.9 | Petkin-Paw_Wipes_Orange Branded SP | **$1.65** |\n| 6 | green pet shop cooling mat | 25.8% | $1.22 | 13.2 | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP | **$1.40** |\n| 7 | B07P6SNV19 (ASIN query) | 47.0% | $0.39 | 23.5 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large Branded SP (ASIN-PT rather than keyword exact) | **$0.45** (PT bid) |\n| 8 | big and thick pet wipes for dogs | 31.3% | $1.98 | 3.1 | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large Branded SP | **$2.30** |\n| 9 | hornady gun safe | 6.6% | $1.15 | 8.5 | Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes Branded SP | **$1.35** |\n| 10 | the green pet shop dog cooling mat | 22.3% | $1.39 | 9.6 | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP | **$1.60** |\n\n## How the bids were set\n\nStarting bid = **observed CPC × 1.15** (15% markup to ensure the new EXACT keyword is competitive enough to win exact-query auctions).\n\nException: for ASIN queries like `B07P6SNV19`, the right structure is a **Product-Targeting (PT) target against that specific competitor ASIN**, not a keyword. The PT bid can start lower (here $0.45) because PT auctions are typically less competitive than keyword auctions on a competitor ASIN.\n\n## Why these specifically\n\nAll 10 terms meet these criteria:\n- Converting at ROAS ≥ 3 (mostly much higher — 10–23×).\n- Not already running as EXACT (or has very few EXACT orders).\n- CPC at or below $2.00 on average.\n- Currently matched through broad/phrase with waste on non-matching queries.\n\nPromoting to EXACT captures the head variant at a cleaner CPC and lets the broad group continue discovery on variants.\n\n## Expected impact\nCombined these 10 search terms currently generate ~$37K in ad-attributed sales at ~$3K spend via broad/phrase matching. Promoting to EXACT:\n- Captures the exact-query auction at lower CPC (typically 10–20% CPC savings on the head term).\n- Broad group continues discovering variants.\n- Net effect: **~$500–1,000/mo in spend savings, and the opportunity to scale these EXACT keywords +25% bid over the starting bid if ACOS holds**.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Current keyword bids** in the destination campaigns — to confirm the new EXACT bid is within the competitive range for that campaign.\n- **Daily search-term trend** — to distinguish chronic winners from recent surges.\n- **Existing negative keywords** — to pre-check whether the new EXACT would be blocked by an existing negative.\n- **Ad-group structure** of the destination campaigns — to know whether they can host an additional EXACT ad group or need a new campaign.\n- **Brand Analytics share-of-voice** on these terms — to size the upside realistically.\n"
