          "label": "Opus 4.7",
          "content": "# 5 Placement-Modifier Opportunities\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-08 (30 days)**.\n- Sources: placement_report (adSlot.type empty in the downloaded file — see caveat) + campaign_performance with top-of-search impression share.\n\n## Caveat on data\nThe `adSlot.type` field in the placement report came back empty, so true TOS / PDP / REST-of-search performance-level splits are not in this data. I therefore use **`metric.topOfSearchImpressionShare`** (from campaign_performance) as the best available signal, combined with campaign-level ACOS. Values of TOS share > 100% in the raw field look like a unit / scaling artifact in this particular report; I treat the field as an ordinal signal rather than a literal percent.\n\n## 5 candidate campaigns for TOS-modifier adjustment\n\n### **Decrease TOS modifier (top-of-search bidding too aggressive relative to performance)**\n\n| # | Campaign (trunc.) | Spend | ACOS | TOS signal | Proposed action |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes MULTI NB SP Phrase | $1,551 | **116%** | High | **Cut TOS modifier to 0%** (ACOS 116% — top-of-search is not paying off) |\n| 2 | Petkin-Paw_Wipes_Orange MULTI NB SP Exact | $929 | 95% | High | **Cut TOS modifier by 50–70%** |\n| 3 | Petkin-Pet_Dental_Wipes MULTI NB SP Exact | $762 | 81% | High | **Cut TOS modifier by 50–70%** |\n| 4 | Hornady-Auto_Charge_Pro_Powder_Measure NB SP EXACT | $616 | 69% | High | **Cut TOS modifier to 0%** — consider also reviewing the keyword targeting (EV186 flagged multiple keywords in this campaign as 0-converters) |\n| 5 | Hornady-Fireproof_Keypad_Safe B09TQ2CW9L NB SP Phrase | $583 | 56% | High | **Cut TOS modifier by 40%** |\n\nAll five have ACOS far above the account target (19.3%) while concentrating significant impression share at top-of-search. That's the classic \"TOS modifier is too aggressive\" symptom.\n\n### **Increase TOS modifier (opportunity — good ACOS but low TOS share)**\n\n| # | Campaign (trunc.) | Spend | ACOS | TOS signal | Proposed action |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| 6 | Hornady-Fireproof_Keypad_Safe B09TQ2CW9L NB SP Auto | $846 | 14% | **Low** (~22%) | **Add TOS modifier of +25–50%** |\n\nOnly one campaign cleanly fits \"low TOS share + ACOS well under target\". It's performing at 14% ACOS (well below the 19.3% target), so there's headroom to bid aggressively into top-of-search without breaking economics.\n\n## Justification by placement breakdown (what the question asks for)\n\nThe question asks each recommendation be justified \"with the placement breakdown\". The placement breakdown itself is not populated in the downloaded report (`adSlot.type` is empty), but the top-of-search impression-share signal plus campaign ACOS lets us rank the candidates:\n\n- **High ACOS + concentrated TOS share** → cut TOS modifier.\n- **Low ACOS + dispersed TOS share** → raise TOS modifier.\n\nA proper placement-breakdown-based justification requires:\n- TOS placement ACOS = spend at TOS / sales at TOS.\n- PDP placement ACOS = spend at PDP / sales at PDP.\n- REST placement ACOS = spend at REST / sales at REST.\n\nWith those three numbers, the recommendation would be: \"campaign X shows TOS ACOS = 35%, PDP ACOS = 12%, REST ACOS = 18% — reduce TOS modifier to 0%\". The direction is the same as inferred here, but the exact magnitude would be calibrated.\n\n## Expected impact (directional)\n\nCutting TOS modifiers on #1–#5 (combined $4,441 in spend at 85% blended ACOS) by 50% on average:\n- Spend reduction: ~$1,000/mo.\n- Sales reduction: ~$300/mo (proportional to the portion of spend that was inefficient TOS).\n- Blended ACOS of this cohort drops from 85% to ~50%.\n\nIncreasing TOS modifier on #6 (spend $846 at 14% ACOS):\n- Additional spend: ~$200–400/mo.\n- Additional sales: ~$1,500–3,000/mo (at 14% ACOS).\n\nNet: **~$500 less in monthly spend, $1K–$2K more in monthly sales**.\n\n## What I still don't have\n\n- **Real placement-level performance breakdown** (TOS / PDP / REST sales and spend). The report's `adSlot.type` field returned empty in the download — critical for precise modifier magnitude.\n- **Current TOS / PDP / REST modifier values** for each campaign — without these, \"cut 50%\" can't be translated to an absolute percentage change.\n- **SB / SBV placement modifiers** — the analysis here is SP-focused.\n- **Per-campaign impression-share trend** — to check whether the high-TOS campaigns have been high-TOS forever or it's a recent drift.\n- **Organic top-of-search ranking** — if the ASIN is organically ranking #1 for these terms, an aggressive TOS modifier may be double-buying the same placement.\n"
