          "content": "# 5 ASINs Receiving Below-Average Ad Spend Relative to Their Order Volume\n\n## Data Window\n- **Period:** 2026-04-09 to 2026-05-08 (30 days)\n- **Account:** Firefly Buys (`amzn1.ads-account.g.bj313q92siafngzbl54ewi56r`)\n- **Campaign report rows:** 148 (across 148 unique campaigns)\n- **ASIN report rows:** 941 (across 311 unique ASINs)\n- **Total account ad spend:** $52,851.62\n- **Weighted average CPO (Cost Per Order):** $9.22\n\n## Methodology\n\nSpend was allocated to ASINs proportionally: for each campaign, its total spend was distributed to the ASINs that generated orders within that campaign, in proportion to each ASIN's share of that campaign's order count. This gives an estimated ad spend per ASIN, from which a Cost Per Order (CPO) is derived.\n\nASINs with CPO significantly below the account-wide weighted average ($9.22) are **under-invested relative to their order velocity** — they convert efficiently but receive less ad support than peers. The 5 ASINs below were selected by a composite score of `order volume × % CPO gap`, surfacing those where both volume and underspend are large.\n\nThe recommended spend increase targets bringing each ASIN's CPO to the account average over the same 30-day period, expressed as both a total 30-day increment and a daily budget addition.\n\n---\n\n## Top 5 Under-Invested ASINs\n\n| # | ASIN | Orders (30d) | Current Spend | CPO | Avg CPO | Gap | ROAS | Recommended Increase | +$/day |\n|---|------|:---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| 1 | **B07R4BSY17** | 240 | $1,230.75 | $5.13 | $9.22 | −44% | 3.01× | **+$982** | +$32.7 |\n| 2 | **B07BR7ZLZZ** | 128 | $515.47 | $4.03 | $9.22 | −56% | 5.50× | **+$664** | +$22.1 |\n| 3 | **B0001NA29U** | 68 | $221.73 | $3.24 | $9.22 | −65% | 6.46× | **+$407** | +$13.6 |\n| 4 | **B07QM2T4NK** | 70 | $253.00 | $3.61 | $9.22 | −61% | 13.18× | **+$393** | +$13.1 |\n| 5 | **B007TNXGMK** | 75 | $347.51 | $4.72 | $9.22 | −49% | 5.12× | **+$337** | +$11.2 |\n\n---\n\n## ASIN-Level Detail & Rationale\n\n### 1. B07R4BSY17 — Recommend +$982 (+$33/day)\n- **240 orders / $3,702.53 in sales** on only $1,230.75 spend — highest absolute order volume among underspent ASINs.\n- CPO of $5.13 is 44% below the account average, meaning this ASIN converts nearly twice as efficiently as the typical campaign.\n- ROAS of 3.01× is positive; incremental spend here is likely profitable.\n- **Action:** Increase daily budget by ~$33 on campaigns featuring this ASIN.\n\n### 2. B07BR7ZLZZ — Recommend +$664 (+$22/day)\n- **128 orders / $2,836.71 in sales** on $515.47 spend — CPO of $4.03 is 56% below average.\n- ROAS of 5.50× indicates strong return; ad spend is disproportionately low vs. conversion rate.\n- **Action:** Increase daily budget by ~$22 on campaigns featuring this ASIN.\n\n### 3. B0001NA29U — Recommend +$407 (+$14/day)\n- **68 orders / $1,423.80 in sales** on only $221.73 spend — CPO of $3.24 is 65% below average.\n- ROAS of 6.46× is excellent; this ASIN is severely under-funded relative to its efficiency.\n- **Action:** Increase daily budget by ~$14 on campaigns featuring this ASIN.\n\n### 4. B07QM2T4NK — Recommend +$393 (+$13/day)\n- **70 orders / $3,329.26 in sales** on $253.00 spend — CPO of $3.61 is 61% below average.\n- ROAS of **13.18×** is the highest among the top candidates — every dollar spent returns $13 in attributed sales.\n- **Action:** Increase daily budget by ~$13 on campaigns featuring this ASIN; this is the highest-return opportunity.\n\n### 5. B007TNXGMK — Recommend +$337 (+$11/day)\n- **75 orders / $1,813.05 in sales** on $347.51 spend — CPO of $4.72 is 49% below average.\n- ROAS of 5.12× is solid; this ASIN has consistent order volume but is not being fully funded.\n- **Action:** Increase daily budget by ~$11 on campaigns featuring this ASIN.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Total recommended additional spend (30d) | **+$2,783** |\n|---|---|\n| Combined additional daily budget | **+$92.7/day** |\n| Expected additional orders if conversion rates hold | ~302 |\n\nB07QM2T4NK should be prioritized first given its 13.18× ROAS — it has the most compelling return on incremental spend. B07BR7ZLZZ and B0001NA29U follow as the most CPO-efficient ASINs in absolute terms.\n"
