          "content": "# Budget Reallocation — 3 to Reduce, 3 to Receive\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **2026-04-09 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**, 148 campaigns.\n\n## 3 campaigns to REDUCE (high spend + very high ACOS)\n\n| # | Campaign | Current spend | Sales | ACOS | Proposed budget cut |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| 1 | SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box NB SP Phrase | $310 | $169 | **183%** | **−$250** (pause or cap at $60) |\n| 2 | SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box NB CNQ SP CAT | $249 | $151 | **165%** | **−$200** (pause or cap at $50) |\n| 3 | Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes MULTI NB SP Phrase | $285 | $174 | **164%** | **−$225** (pause or cap at $60) |\n| **Total reduction** | | | | | **−$675/mo** |\n\n### Why these 3\nAll three spend meaningfully ($250–310/mo) at ACOS above 150% — they're losing money on every sale. The two SnapSafe campaigns both target the same single ASIN (`B06XQVYY24`) and both underperform — this product line has a core problem (likely price/margin or listing relevance on the Treklite Gun Safe Lock Box) that no amount of bidding change will fix. The Petkin PHRASE campaign shows the same \"low AOV product on broad match\" pattern flagged in EV184.\n\n### What to do with the reduced campaigns\n- **SnapSafe Treklite** (both variants): pause while reviewing the ASIN's price / listing against category competitors. Don't just reduce budget — 165–183% ACOS means the product can't economically compete at the current CPC; reducing budget merely slows the bleeding.\n- **Petkin MegaValuPak Phrase**: switch from PHRASE to EXACT on the top 5 converting search terms; negate the rest.\n\n## 3 campaigns to RECEIVE the freed budget (low ACOS at scale)\n\n| # | Campaign | Current spend | Sales | ACOS | Proposed budget increase |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| 1 | **GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP Phrase** | $2,224 | $31,760 | **7%** | **+$400** (to $2,624/mo) |\n| 2 | **GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pads MULTI NB SB Exact** | $1,006 | $8,419 | **12%** | **+$200** (to $1,206/mo) |\n| 3 | **Hornady-Fireproof_Keypad_Safe B09TQ2CW9L NB SP Auto** | $846 | $5,858 | **14%** | **+$150** (to $996/mo) |\n| **Total increase** | | | | | **+$750/mo** |\n\n### Why these 3\n- **GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded Phrase (7% ACOS)**: account's single best ROAS campaign. 14× ROAS, branded-query driven, very scalable.\n- **GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pads SB Exact (12% ACOS)**: SB-driven — NTB-generating, aligned with EV171's finding that SB is the NTB engine.\n- **Hornady-Fireproof_Keypad_Safe Auto (14% ACOS)**: the auto campaign is the one Hornady safe campaign that works well, in contrast to the many Hornady NB Phrase / EXACT campaigns that underperform. Let the auto campaign keep harvesting efficient search terms.\n\n## Justification summary\n\n| Side | Reasoning |\n|---|---|\n| **Cuts** | 3 campaigns at ACOS ≥ 164% — structurally unprofitable even if they convert; net-loss on every sale |\n| **Increases** | 3 campaigns at ACOS ≤ 14% — substantially below account blended (19.3%); have demonstrated scale (clicks 300–1,890) and stable conversion |\n\n## Expected net impact\n- Monthly spend change: **+$75 net** ($750 added − $675 removed).\n- Monthly sales change: **+$4,500 net** (~$6,000 added at avg 12% ACOS vs −$500 of genuinely low-quality revenue removed).\n- Blended ACOS drops by ~0.3 pp.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Budget caps** on each of the 6 campaigns — needed to know whether the recommended increase fits under the current cap.\n- **Portfolio-level budgets** — any of these campaigns might be capped by their portfolio rather than by their own daily budget.\n- **Xnurta AI target ACOS** per campaign — if the auto-bidder is throttling the winners, raising budget won't help until target-ACOS is loosened.\n- **Daily delivery status** — to confirm the 3 winners are actually budget-constrained and not just under-bidding.\n- **Inventory for GPS Cool_Pet_Pad ASINs** — before scaling the Phrase Branded campaign, confirm stock can support the volume increase.\n"
