          "label": "Insight Agent",
          "content": "> **Assumptions applied:** No time range was specified, so this analysis covers the last 30 days (Apr 9 – May 8, 2026). Reallocation candidates are drawn from **enabled campaigns only**. Reduction candidates = high ACOS / low ROAS + budget surplus (utilization < 70%); Increase candidates = low ACOS / high ROAS + budget-constrained (utilization > 85%). If these assumptions don't match your intent, please let me know and I'll adjust.\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Key Takeaways\n\n1. **$1,995 in budget can be freed** from 3 campaigns that have spent $0 over the past 30 days — their entire allocated budget is sitting idle.\n2. **All 3 increase candidates are branded campaigns** with exceptional ROAS (18.9×–19.1×) and ACOS below 6%, yet they are hitting their daily budget caps.\n3. **The reallocation is highly asymmetric in scale**: the largest single reduction ($1,500 from one campaign) alone covers 75% of the total freed budget.\n4. **One increase candidate (WineRX SB)** shows a utilization rate of 303%, indicating it is significantly over-pacing its $1/day budget — this is the most urgent case for a budget increase.\n\n---\n\n## 📉 Campaigns to Reduce Budget (3 Campaigns)\n\n**Portfolio benchmark (spend-weighted):** ACOS = 19.07% | ROAS = 5.24×\n\n\n| Campaign Name | Type | Daily Budget (USD) | 30d Spend (USD) | Budget Utilization | ACOS | ROAS | Suggested Reduction (USD) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"PerfectBungee-Catch_All-Branded-CatAsin\">PerfectBungee-Catch_All-Branded-CatAsin</Link> | sponsoredProducts | 15 | 0 | 0 |  |  | 225 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase\">GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase</Link> | sponsoredProducts | 100 | 0 | 0 |  |  | 1500 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"PerfectBungee-Standard_PC_Multi_Pack_8ct-B07VHLGLBZ-Branded-Phrase\">PerfectBungee-Standard_PC_Multi_Pack_8ct-B07VHLGLBZ-Branded-Phrase</Link> | sponsoredProducts | 18 | 0 | 0 |  |  | 270 |\n\n### Reduction Rationale\n\nAll three campaigns recorded **zero spend over the full 30-day window**, meaning their budgets are entirely unused. The suggested reduction frees up **50% of the idle budget** (i.e., 50% of daily budget × 30 days), leaving the remaining half as a buffer in case activity resumes.\n\n| Campaign | Why Reduce | Freed Budget |\n|---|---|---|\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase\">GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase</Link> | $0 spend in 30 days on a $100/day budget — 0% utilization, no measurable return | **$1,500** |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"PerfectBungee-Standard_PC_Multi_Pack_8ct-B07VHLGLBZ-Branded-Phrase\">PerfectBungee-Standard_PC_Multi_Pack_8ct-B07VHLGLBZ-Branded-Phrase</Link> | $0 spend in 30 days on an $18/day budget — 0% utilization, no measurable return | **$270** |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"PerfectBungee-Catch_All-Branded-CatAsin\">PerfectBungee-Catch_All-Branded-CatAsin</Link> | $0 spend in 30 days on a $15/day budget — 0% utilization, no measurable return | **$225** |\n| **Total freed** | | **$1,995** |\n\n> ⚠️ **Note:** Zero spend may indicate targeting issues, paused ad groups within the campaign, or no eligible inventory — it is worth investigating the root cause before or alongside the budget reduction.\n\n---\n\n## 📈 Campaigns to Increase Budget (3 Campaigns)\n\n\n| Campaign Name | Type | Daily Budget (USD) | 30d Spend (USD) | Budget Utilization | ACOS | ROAS | Suggested Increase (USD) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball-MULTI-Branded-SP-EXACT\">GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball-MULTI-Branded-SP-EXACT</Link> | sponsoredProducts | 5 | 128.03 | 0.85 | 5.25 | 19.06 | 668 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN\">Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN</Link> | sponsoredProducts | 5 | 149.09 | 0.99 | 5.28 | 18.95 | 664 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT\">WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT</Link> | sponsoredBrands | 1 | 90.93 | 3.03 | 5.29 | 18.91 | 663 |\n\n### Increase Rationale\n\nAll three campaigns are **top performers** — their ROAS is 3.6×–3.6× above the account average (19× vs. 5.24×) and their ACOS is less than one-third of the account average (5.3% vs. 19.1%). Yet they are running on very tight daily budgets ($1–$5/day) and are clearly budget-constrained.\n\nThe $1,995 freed budget is distributed proportionally by ROAS:\n\n| Campaign | Why Increase | Suggested Increase | New Monthly Budget |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball-MULTI-Branded-SP-EXACT\">GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball-MULTI-Branded-SP-EXACT</Link> | ROAS 19.06× (3.6× account avg), ACOS 5.25%, 85% utilization — hitting cap regularly | **+$668** | ~$818 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN\">Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN</Link> | ROAS 18.95× (3.6× account avg), ACOS 5.28%, 99% utilization — nearly fully constrained | **+$664** | ~$814 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT\">WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT</Link> | ROAS 18.91× (3.6× account avg), ACOS 5.29%, 303% utilization — severely underfunded relative to demand | **+$663** | ~$693 |\n| **Total allocated** | | **$1,995** | |\n\n> 💡 **Implementation note:** The suggested increase amounts are expressed as **30-day totals**. To apply them, divide by 30 to get the daily budget increment (e.g., +$668 ÷ 30 ≈ **+$22/day** for GuardianSports). For the WineRX SB campaign, given its 303% utilization on a $1/day budget, even a modest daily increase to $23/day would be transformative.\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Reallocation Summary\n\n\n| Direction | Campaign | Amount (30d) |\n|---|---|---|\n| ➖ Reduce | <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase\">GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase</Link> | −$1,500 |\n| ➖ Reduce | <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"PerfectBungee-Standard_PC_Multi_Pack_8ct-B07VHLGLBZ-Branded-Phrase\">PerfectBungee-Standard_PC_Multi_Pack_8ct-B07VHLGLBZ-Branded-Phrase</Link> | −$270 |\n| ➖ Reduce | <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"PerfectBungee-Catch_All-Branded-CatAsin\">PerfectBungee-Catch_All-Branded-CatAsin</Link> | −$225 |\n| ➕ Increase | <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball-MULTI-Branded-SP-EXACT\">GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball-MULTI-Branded-SP-EXACT</Link> | +$668 |\n| ➕ Increase | <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN\">Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN</Link> | +$664 |\n| ➕ Increase | <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT\">WineRX-Drop_It_Wine_Drops-BRANDED-SB-EXACT</Link> | +$663 |\n| **Net** | | **$0** |"
