          "label": "GPT 5.5",
          "content": "# ASIN Pause Candidates After 60 Days\n\nQuestion: ASINs that should be paused from ads (sustained zero or negligible sales over 60+ days at meaningful spend).\n\nBusiness data used: campaign-level advertising performance, ASIN/product-level attributed sales and orders, ad-product/ad-type performance across SP/SB/SD, campaign configuration, budget, and status snapshots。 Time basis: 2026-03-10/2026-05-08; 2026-03-10/2026-05-07; 2026-03-11/2026-05-07。 Monetary values follow the numeric currency basis present in the business data; no additional FX conversion was applied.\n\nNote: This answer was regenerated using the richer ZH business data for the same question while keeping the output in English.\n\n## Executive Read\n\nUsing the richer business data for this question, measurable totals are spend $84,430.06, sales $469,997.90, orders 10,901, clicks 65,708, and aggregate ACOS 18.0%. The analysis below focuses on the most relevant ASIN dimension for the question.\n\n## Period / Business View Comparison\n\n| business view / period | rows | spend | sales | orders | ACOS | ROAS |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Business slice 1 | 1,310 | $0.00 | $469,997.90 | 10,901 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| Business slice 2 | 161 | $84,225.77 | $0.00 | 0 | n/a | 0.00 |\n| Business slice 3 | 2 | $204.29 | $0.00 | 0 | n/a | 0.00 |\n\n## Key ASIN View\n\n| ASIN | spend | sales | orders | clicks | ACOS | CVR |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| B006NONHNE | $0.00 | $27,679.37 | 447 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0C5MYTF7W | $0.00 | $22,520.20 | 370 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B006NOO440 | $0.00 | $18,884.74 | 213 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B07XPGKJKM | $0.00 | $14,382.10 | 274 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0G2Y26PSL | $0.00 | $14,320.80 | 157 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0G2YJ9KK2 | $0.00 | $12,999.82 | 209 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0C5MY7MNL | $0.00 | $12,909.96 | 152 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0C5N3713P | $0.00 | $12,332.52 | 239 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n\n## Scale Candidates\n\n| ASIN | spend | sales | orders | clicks | ACOS | recommendation |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| B006NONHNE | $0.00 | $27,679.37 | 447 | 0 | 0.0% | protect budget and expand exact/high-intent coverage |\n| B0C5MYTF7W | $0.00 | $22,520.20 | 370 | 0 | 0.0% | protect budget and expand exact/high-intent coverage |\n| B006NOO440 | $0.00 | $18,884.74 | 213 | 0 | 0.0% | protect budget and expand exact/high-intent coverage |\n| B07XPGKJKM | $0.00 | $14,382.10 | 274 | 0 | 0.0% | protect budget and expand exact/high-intent coverage |\n| B0G2Y26PSL | $0.00 | $14,320.80 | 157 | 0 | 0.0% | protect budget and expand exact/high-intent coverage |\n| B0G2YJ9KK2 | $0.00 | $12,999.82 | 209 | 0 | 0.0% | protect budget and expand exact/high-intent coverage |\n\n## Optimization / Reduction Candidates\n\n| ASIN | spend | sales | orders | clicks | ACOS | recommended action |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| N/A | $21.62 | $0.00 | 0 | 0 | n/a | negate, pause, or reduce bid after checking strategic value |\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. Reallocate budget toward entities with orders, controlled ACOS, and stable sales contribution.\n2. Reduce or pause high-spend zero-order entities first to release inefficient spend.\n3. For entities with orders but high ACOS, lower bids by 15-30% and monitor for 3-5 days.\n4. If the requested bid, budget, placement, or advertised-ASIN fields are missing from the business data, add those fields before making exact operational changes.\n"
