          "content": "# Quarterly Forecast: Q3 2026 Spend, Sales & ACOS\n\n## Data Window\n\n| Period | Dates | Days | Report Rows |\n|--------|-------|------|-------------|\n| Period 1 | 2026-02-08 – 2026-02-28 | 21 | 147 |\n| Period 2 | 2026-03-01 – 2026-03-31 | 31 | 150 |\n| Period 3 | 2026-04-01 – 2026-05-08 | 38 | 154 |\n| **Trailing 90-day total** | **2026-02-08 – 2026-05-08** | **90** | **451** |\n\nAccount: **Firefly Buys** (`amzn1.ads-account.g.bj313q92siafngzbl54ewi56r`) — all currencies in USD.\n\n---\n\n## Trailing-90-Day Actuals\n\n| Metric | Period 1 (Feb 8–28) | Period 2 (Mar) | Period 3 (Apr 1–May 8) | **90-Day Total** |\n|--------|---------------------|----------------|------------------------|-----------------|\n| Days | 21 | 31 | 38 | 90 |\n| Spend | $27,459 | $29,782 | $63,426 | **$120,667** |\n| Sales | $148,144 | $188,742 | $336,890 | **$673,776** |\n| ACOS | 18.5% | 15.8% | 18.8% | **17.9%** |\n| Daily Spend | $1,308/day | $961/day | $1,669/day | $1,341/day avg |\n| Daily Sales | $7,054/day | $6,088/day | $8,866/day | $7,486/day avg |\n| Purchases | 3,500 | 5,100 | 7,229 | 15,829 |\n| Impressions | 2,697,807 | 3,080,538 | 6,639,689 | 12,418,034 |\n| Clicks | 20,638 | 25,376 | 47,827 | 93,841 |\n\n---\n\n## Forecast: Q3 2026 (July 1 – September 30, 92 days)\n\n| Metric | Projected Q3 2026 |\n|--------|-------------------|\n| **Spend** | **$154,007** |\n| **Sales** | **$841,544** |\n| **ACOS** | **~18.3%** |\n\n---\n\n## Methodology & Assumptions\n\n### 1. Trend Model — Linear Regression on Daily Rates\n\nRather than using raw monthly totals (which are distorted by the unequal number of days in each period), I normalised to **daily rates** per period and fitted a simple linear regression across three consecutive periods (index 0, 1, 2), then projected forward to period index 3 (next quarter).\n\n| Metric | P1 Daily | P2 Daily | P3 Daily | Slope per period | P4 Forecast |\n|--------|----------|----------|----------|-----------------|-------------|\n| Spend/day | $1,308 | $961 | $1,669 | **+$181/period** | $1,674/day |\n| Sales/day | $7,054 | $6,088 | $8,866 | **+$906/period** | $9,147/day |\n| ACOS | 18.5% | 15.8% | 18.8% | **+0.15 pp/period** | 18.3% |\n\n**Q3 projection = forecast daily rate × 92 days.**\n\n### 2. Explicit Assumptions\n\n| # | Assumption | Rationale |\n|---|------------|-----------|\n| A1 | **Linear trend holds** | Three periods show an upward trajectory in both spend and sales with Period 3 notably higher (38-day window including ramp-up). Linear extrapolation is the simplest defensible model given only 3 data points. |\n| A2 | **Seasonal effects are modest** | Q3 (Jul–Sep) is typically a mid-strength quarter for e-commerce. No holiday spike (that would be Q4). Forecast may be slightly conservative if Prime Day (typically July) drives a sales spike. |\n| A3 | **Campaign mix stays constant** | No new campaigns launched, no major budget reallocation assumed. |\n| A4 | **No budget cap constraints** | Spend is allowed to scale proportionally with the observed trend. |\n| A5 | **ACOS remains ~18%** | ACOS has been stable (15.8–18.8%) across the trailing window; the slight upward regression slope (+0.15 pp/period) is small and unlikely to materially shift the ratio. |\n| A6 | **Currency = USD throughout** | All budgets and sales reported in USD. |\n\n### 3. Confidence Caveats\n\n- Only **3 monthly data points** are available; regression uncertainty is high. Results are directional, not precise.\n- Period 3 (Apr 1–May 8, 38 days) is the most recent and carries the most weight in the trend — the ~75% jump in daily spend vs. Period 2 is a strong signal but could partially reflect a campaign launch or budget increase rather than organic growth.\n- If the Period 3 spike is anomalous, the flat-trend (trailing 90-day average) scenario gives a more conservative estimate:\n  - **Conservative scenario**: $1,341/day × 92 days = **$123,372 spend**, $7,486/day × 92 = **$688,712 sales**, ACOS ~17.9%.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Scenario | Q3 Spend | Q3 Sales | Q3 ACOS |\n|----------|----------|----------|---------|\n| **Trend-linear (base case)** | **$154,007** | **$841,544** | **18.3%** |\n| Conservative (trailing avg) | $123,372 | $688,712 | 17.9% |\n\nThe base-case forecast projects **~28% growth in spend and ~25% growth in sales** quarter-over-quarter, with ACOS holding roughly flat at ~18%. The primary risk factor is whether the Period 3 acceleration is sustained trend or a one-time step-up.\n"
