          "content": "# Should I Pause This Campaign?\n\n> **No specific campaign was named.** The question was asked without specifying which campaign to evaluate. Rather than asking for clarification, this analysis identifies all campaigns with poor performance over the last 30 days so you can decide which ones to pause.\n\n---\n\n## Data Window\n\n- **Period:** 2026-04-09 to 2026-05-08 (30 days)\n- **Account:** Firefly Buys (`amzn1.ads-account.g.bj313q92siafngzbl54ewi56r`) — US marketplace\n- **Report rows:** 148 (one row per campaign, aggregated across the full period)\n- **Unique campaigns with spend:** 148\n\n---\n\n## Portfolio Summary\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Total Spend | $52,851.22 |\n| Total Sales | $277,580.55 |\n| Overall ROAS | **5.25x** |\n| Total Purchases | 5,752 |\n| Total Impressions | 5,493,846 |\n| Total Clicks | 39,170 |\n\nThe account as a whole is healthy (5.25x ROAS). However, several individual campaigns are significantly dragging down profitability.\n\n---\n\n## Pause Candidates — Ranked by Urgency\n\n### Tier 1: Strong pause recommendations (ROAS < 0.75 or zero sales with meaningful spend)\n\n| Campaign | Spend | Sales | ROAS | ACoS | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Hornady-LockNLoad_Hot_Tub_Sonic_Cleaner-NB-SP-Exact** | $134.02 | $0.00 | 0.00x | — | 66 clicks, zero conversions |\n| **SnapSafe-Treklite_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-SP-Phrase** | $309.92 | $169.16 | 0.55x | 183% | Losing $0.45 per $1 spent |\n| **SnapSafe-Treklite_Lock_Box-MULTI-NB-SP-Auto** | $334.17 | $246.74 | 0.74x | 135% | Auto campaign with poor conversion |\n| **Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase** | $155.64 | $63.84 | 0.41x | 244% | Losing $0.59 per $1 spent |\n| **Arrow-Home_Products_Fiesta_Taco_Plate-NB-SP-Phrase** | $79.87 | $33.96 | 0.43x | 235% | Losing $0.57 per $1 spent |\n| **SnapSafe-Treklite_Lock_Box-NB-CNQ-SP-CAT** | $248.59 | $150.71 | 0.61x | 165% | Category targeting not converting |\n\n### Tier 2: Consider pausing or optimizing (ROAS 0.75–1.0)\n\n| Campaign | Spend | Sales | ROAS | ACoS | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase** | $1,550.51 | $1,335.27 | 0.86x | 116% | Highest absolute loss: –$215/30 days |\n| **Petkin-Pet_Fingertip_Tooth_Wipes-NB-SP-Exact** | $467.62 | $419.18 | 0.90x | 112% | Marginally unprofitable |\n| **Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact** | $338.63 | $306.02 | 0.90x | 111% | Marginally unprofitable |\n| **Petkin-Pet_Dental_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase** | $408.60 | $381.27 | 0.93x | 107% | Marginally unprofitable |\n| **Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase** | $498.87 | $467.61 | 0.94x | 107% | Marginally unprofitable |\n| **Hornady-Rapid_Safe_Night_Guard-NB-CNQ-SP-CAT** | $233.78 | $194.95 | 0.83x | 120% | Category targeting not converting |\n| **DelkProducts-FrostGuard_All-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact** | $103.21 | $100.96 | 0.98x | 102% | Near breakeven |\n\n### Tier 3: Zero-sales campaigns with small spend (monitor or pause)\n\nThese have spent under $30 each with zero sales — likely seasonal or new products with low traffic. Review product listing quality before pausing.\n\n| Campaign | Spend | Clicks | Impressions |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| DelkProducts-FrostGuard_Vortex_Puppy_Paws_Standard | $29.94 | 29 | 2,948 |\n| DelkProducts-Frostguard-Plus_Black_XL (SBV) | $27.53 | 29 | 2,104 |\n| DelkProducts-FrostGuard-Deluxe Brand KW Branded | $15.28 | 19 | 1,653 |\n| SnapSafe-Vault_Door_OffWhite Branded | $15.05 | 23 | 1,693 |\n| DelkProducts-FrostGuard_Vortex_Black_Standard | $13.52 | 15 | 3,271 |\n\n---\n\n## Top Single Pause Recommendation\n\nIf you can only act on one campaign: **pause `Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase`**.\n\n- It is the **largest absolute money-loser** at –$215.24 net over 30 days ($1,550.51 spend vs. $1,335.27 in attributed sales).\n- ROAS of 0.86x (ACoS 116%) indicates the campaign is generating clicks but failing to convert at a profitable rate.\n- The corresponding Exact match campaign (`Hornady-Fireproof_Safe-NB-SP-Exact`) has ROAS of 3.07x on similar traffic — the keyword or match type in the Phrase campaign is likely pulling in less-qualified traffic.\n\n**Recommended action:** Pause the Phrase match campaign, harvest any converting search terms, and add them as Exact targets to the profitable Exact campaign.\n\n---\n\n## Reasoning\n\n- **Pause threshold used:** ROAS < 1.0 (spending more than earning back in attributed sales). Campaigns below 1.0x ROAS are unprofitable on a direct revenue basis, before factoring in cost of goods.\n- **Absolute loss weighted:** Higher-spend campaigns with ROAS just below 1.0 (e.g., Hornady Gun Safes Phrase at –$215) are more urgent than small-spend campaigns with worse ROAS but negligible dollar impact.\n- **Context caveat:** ACoS/ROAS alone don't capture full profitability (margins vary by product). For low-margin products, even a ROAS of 2–3x may be unprofitable; for high-margin products, a ROAS of 0.9x might be acceptable if it drives new-to-brand customers. Validate against your target ACoS per product category before pausing.\n"
