          "label": "Gemini 3.1 Pro",
          "content": "# Ad Spend Distribution by ASIN\n\n## Analysis Overview\nThis report breaks down the total ad spend across individual ASINs to identify concentration risk and spending efficiency. We analyze the degree to which budget is concentrated among top-performing products versus a distributed long-tail strategy.\n\n---\n\n## Spending Distribution Summary\n\n| Segment | ASIN Count | Total Spend ($) | Spend Share (%) | Sales Share (%) | ACOS |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Top 10 ASINs** | 10 | $26,358 | 48.5% | 43.4% | 25.1% |\n| **Next 11–50 ASINs** | 40 | $15,219 | 28.0% | 31.2% | 19.5% |\n| **Long Tail (51+)** | 261 | $12,777 | 23.5% | 25.4% | 21.2% |\n| **Total** | **311** | **$54,354** | **100%** | **100%** | **22.4%** |\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations\n\n### 1. High Concentration in the \"Head\"\nThe account's spending is highly concentrated. The **Top 10 ASINs account for nearly 49% of the total budget**.\n- **Top Spender**: `B006NONHNE` alone consumes roughly 7% of the total account budget.\n- **Efficiency Risk**: The Top 10 segment has the highest ACOS (25.1%), indicating that these products are being pushed aggressively into competitive, high-CPC auctions.\n\n### 2. The Efficiency \"Sweet Spot\" (ASINs 11–50)\nThe most efficient spending occurs in the middle segment (ASINs ranked 11–50).\n- This group generates 31% of sales with only 28% of the spend, resulting in an impressive **19.5% ACOS**.\n- **Opportunity**: This suggests that there are many \"Rising Star\" ASINs in this range that could likely handle additional budget while maintaining better efficiency than the current Top 10.\n\n### 3. Broad Long-Tail Coverage\nThe account maintains a very healthy long-tail coverage, with over **260 ASINs** receiving at least some ad support. \n- This diversification provides a stable baseline for the account and ensures brand presence across many niche categories.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion and Recommendations\nThe spend distribution reflects a **\"Top-Heavy\" strategy** where 3% of the products (the Top 10) command 49% of the budget.\n\n**Strategic Directions:**\n1. **Budget Rebalancing**: Consider a tactical shift of 5–10% of the budget from the low-efficiency Top 10 items toward the high-efficiency \"Middle Class\" (ASINs 11–50).\n2. **CPC Caps for Top ASINs**: Implement stricter bid controls on the Top 3 spenders to drive down their combined ACOS toward the account average of 22%.\n3. **Audit Underperformers**: Within the \"Long Tail,\" identify ASINs with >$100 spend and 0 sales over the last 30 days to prune wasted budget.\n"
