          "label": "Opus 4.7",
          "content": "# Halo-Only ASINs (Not Directly Advertised) — Top 10 by Halo Dollars\n\n## Data Window\n- **Date range:** 2026-04-09 → 2026-05-08 (last 30 days)\n- **Source:** Sponsored Products report at `convertedProduct.id` × `campaign.id` granularity, with both `metric.sales` and `metric.salesPromoted`\n- **Rows:** 943 | **Unique ASINs:** 312\n\n## Definition\n- **Promoted sales** (`metric.salesPromoted`) = revenue from purchases of *the exact ASIN that was advertised in the campaign*\n- **Halo sales** = `metric.sales − metric.salesPromoted` = revenue from purchases of *other* ASINs that converted off the same ad impression\n- A \"halo-only\" ASIN has `salesPromoted = $0` across **all** its rows in the report (i.e., it never appears as the directly advertised ASIN, only as an indirect conversion)\n\n## Account-level totals\n\n| Metric | Amount |\n|---|---:|\n| Total ad-attributed sales | **$278,319.70** |\n| Promoted sales (own-ASIN) | $119,355.31 |\n| **Halo sales** | **$158,964.39** (57.1% of total) |\n| Halo-only ASINs | **117** (out of 312) |\n\n> Halo represents 57% of all ad-attributed revenue — this account is doing a *lot* of cross-ASIN spillover work, and 117 ASINs ride entirely on it without their own ad spend.\n\n## Top 10 Halo-Only ASINs\n\n| # | ASIN | Halo $ | Halo orders | Avg price | Source campaigns (representative) |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | **B0G2Y26PSL** | $11,975.08 | 131 | $91.41 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad family (Branded SP, NB SP Auto/Exact/Phrase, +12 more) |\n| 2 | **B0G2YJ9KK2** | $11,710.04 | 188 | $62.29 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad family (Branded SP, NB SP Auto/Exact/Phrase, +14 more) |\n| 3 | **B0G2Y8RC8Y** | $5,718.85 | 110 | $51.99 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad + GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad (+10 more) |\n| 4 | **B0G2YMBV65** | $3,303.17 | 79 | $41.81 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad family (NB SP Exact/Phrase, +10 more) |\n| 5 | **B005JEMARS** | $1,319.34 | 61 | $21.63 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad family (Branded SP, NB SP Auto/Exact, +7 more) |\n| 6 | **B0C5N1KGWJ** | $1,299.48 | 49 | $26.52 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad family (NB SP Exact/Phrase, +10 more) |\n| 7 | **B000PD01NS** | $1,247.90 | 2 | $623.95 | Hornady-Auto_Charge_Pro_Powder_Measure (NB Phrase) + Reloading_Case_Trimmer (Branded Phrase) |\n| 8 | **B0G2Y6YSML** | $1,099.56 | 43 | $25.57 | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad family (NB SP Exact/Phrase, +5 more) |\n| 9 | **B0CN2L4TXB** | $1,079.96 | 4 | $269.99 | GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball (Branded Exact + NB Phrase) |\n| 10 | **B005BE47D6** | $1,018.00 | 2 | $509.00 | Flagpole Farm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit (Branded Exact + Branded Phrase) |\n\n**Top 10 total halo revenue:** $39,771.38\n\n## Worth Adding to the Advertised Set?\n\n### Strong \"Yes\" — promote directly\n\n**Ranks 1–4 + 8 (Green Pet Shop / Chillz / Cool Pet Pad family — B0G2Y26PSL, B0G2YJ9KK2, B0G2Y8RC8Y, B0G2YMBV65, B0G2Y6YSML)**\n- Combined halo: **$33,806** in 30 days, **551 halo orders**\n- Each has 40+ orders → real, repeatable demand, not statistical noise\n- All ride on the *Chillz Pet Pad* / *Cool Pet Pad* family campaigns. They look like color/size variants of the advertised hero ASINs\n- **Recommendation:** add as additional ASIN-targeted SP product ads in the existing Chillz/Cool Pet Pad campaigns (cheap, no new campaign overhead). For the top 2 (B0G2Y26PSL and B0G2YJ9KK2 — each generating > $11K), promote them as their own hero ASIN with dedicated keyword + auto campaigns. They have enough volume to stand alone\n\n**Rank 5 + 6 (B005JEMARS, B0C5N1KGWJ)** — same family, slightly lower volume but still 49–61 orders. Add to existing campaigns.\n\n**Rank 9 (B0CN2L4TXB — Guardian Sports Pearl Lacrosse Ball)** — $1,080 / 4 orders / $270 AOV. Branded campaign halo. Likely a variant of the advertised ball or a high-value bundle. Easy add via ASIN targeting in the existing Pearl Lacrosse Ball campaign — minimal incremental risk.\n\n### Maybe — test before committing budget\n\n**Rank 7 (B000PD01NS — Hornady accessory, $1,248 / 2 orders / $624 AOV)**\n- Halo from *different products'* branded campaigns (Auto Charge Pro powder measure, Reloading Case Trimmer)\n- Only 2 orders, but very high AOV → likely a complementary accessory people add to their cart while reloading-tool shopping\n- **Recommendation:** test a small ASIN-targeted SP campaign on the parent product pages. If it doesn't pull incremental sales (i.e., people would have bought it anyway), pause. The risk: ad spend cannibalizes already-organic basket adds\n\n**Rank 10 (B005BE47D6 — Flagpole Farm Titan kit, $1,018 / 2 orders / $509 AOV)**\n- Pure brand-halo from branded SP — high-intent searcher clicked the kit, bought a related accessory\n- 2 orders is too few to make a budget decision. Watch for another month; if halo stays > $500/month, add as ASIN target on the branded campaigns\n\n### Genuinely organic-only candidates\n\nNone of the top 10 look genuinely organic-only. All 10 are riding on existing ad campaigns within the same product family or brand. The \"organic-only\" label would only apply if an ASIN had high halo dollars from *unrelated* campaigns (which would suggest the ASIN converts on its own once a session is seeded), and even then I'd argue an ASIN-targeted ad would be incremental rather than purely cannibalistic.\n\n## Summary\n\n117 ASINs in this account get halo sales without spending a dollar on ads themselves. The top 10 alone capture **$39,771** in 30-day halo revenue. The clearest opportunity is the **GPS Pet Pad variant cluster (5 of the top 10, $33,806 halo)**: these are sibling SKUs to actively advertised products, and the cheapest move is to add them as ASIN targets in the existing Chillz/Cool Pet Pad campaigns. The remaining 5 are smaller halo numbers but most are still worth either a low-cost add (B0CN2L4TXB) or a small test (B000PD01NS, B005BE47D6).\n\n---\n\n## Is the existing data sufficient to answer this?\n\n**Sufficient to identify the candidates and rank them. Partial for the \"worth advertising?\" judgment.**\n\n**What we can answer with the data we have:**\n- The list of halo-only ASINs and their halo dollars — fully covered (117 ASINs identified, top 10 ranked)\n- Which campaigns drive the halo for each ASIN — campaign names are in the report, so attribution is traceable\n- Whether the halo is concentrated in branded/NB/auto/exact campaigns — visible from the campaign-name patterns\n\n**What we cannot fully answer:**\n\nThe \"should we advertise it directly?\" decision depends on **incrementality**, which the report alone cannot measure:\n\n| To decide | Need |\n|---|---|\n| **Is the ASIN active and in stock?** | Catalog API or Seller/Vendor inventory feed (no point promoting an OOS variant) |\n| **Would direct advertising actually be incremental?** | Organic sales for the same ASIN over the same 30 days. If organic = $20K and halo = $11K, direct ads might cannibalize organic rather than grow total revenue |\n| **Is it profitable to advertise?** | Per-ASIN margin (cost of goods, FBA fees) — high-halo low-margin ASINs may not be worth bidding on at competitive CPCs |\n| **Is it actually a variant or a separate listing?** | The report has `convertedProduct.parentProductId`. We didn't break out parent/child relationships here — doing so would let us tell \"add as ASIN target on the parent campaign\" from \"needs its own campaign\" |\n| **Halo sustainability** | One more 30-day window (60-day comparison) to confirm halo is steady, not driven by a one-off promo on the parent ASIN |\n\n**Quick confidence note:** the top-1 conclusion (the GPS Pet Pad variant cluster is the clear opportunity) holds even without the missing data — the halo dollars and order counts are both high enough that even with realistic cannibalization assumptions the recommendation stands. The bottom-half recommendations (ranks 7–10, with 2–4 orders) are where the missing data really matters.\n"
